2470bool SIInstrInfo::isAlwaysGDS(uint16_t Opcode) const {
2471 return Opcode == AMDGPU::DS_ORDERED_COUNT ||
2472 Opcode == AMDGPU::DS_GWS_INIT ||
2473 Opcode == AMDGPU::DS_GWS_SEMA_V ||
2474 Opcode == AMDGPU::DS_GWS_SEMA_BR ||
2475 Opcode == AMDGPU::DS_GWS_SEMA_P ||
2476 Opcode == AMDGPU::DS_GWS_SEMA_RELEASE_ALL ||
2477 Opcode == AMDGPU::DS_GWS_BARRIER;
2478}
2479
2480bool SIInstrInfo::hasUnwantedEffectsWhenEXECEmpty(const MachineInstr &MI) const {
2481 unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode();
2482
2483 if (MI.mayStore() && isSMRD(MI))
2484 return true; // scalar store or atomic
2485
2486 // This will terminate the function when other lanes may need to continue.
2487 if (MI.isReturn())
2488 return true;
2489
2490 // These instructions cause shader I/O that may cause hardware lockups
2491 // when executed with an empty EXEC mask.
2492 //
2493 // Note: exp with VM = DONE = 0 is automatically skipped by hardware when
2494 // EXEC = 0, but checking for that case here seems not worth it
2495 // given the typical code patterns.
2496 if (Opcode == AMDGPU::S_SENDMSG || Opcode == AMDGPU::S_SENDMSGHALT ||
2497 Opcode == AMDGPU::EXP || Opcode == AMDGPU::EXP_DONE ||
2498 Opcode == AMDGPU::DS_ORDERED_COUNT || Opcode == AMDGPU::S_TRAP)
2499 return true;
2500
2501 if (MI.isCall() || MI.isInlineAsm())
2502 return true; // conservative assumption
2503
2504 // These are like SALU instructions in terms of effects, so it's questionable
2505 // whether we should return true for those.
2506 //
2507 // However, executing them with EXEC = 0 causes them to operate on undefined
2508 // data, which we avoid by returning true here.
2509 if (Opcode == AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32 || Opcode == AMDGPU::V_READLANE_B32)
2510 return true;
2511
2512 return false;
2513}
2514
2515bool SIInstrInfo::mayReadEXEC(const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
2516 const MachineInstr &MI) const {
2517 if (MI.isMetaInstruction())
2518 return false;
2519
2520 // This won't read exec if this is an SGPR->SGPR copy.
2521 if (MI.isCopyLike()) {
2522 if (!RI.isSGPRReg(MRI, MI.getOperand(0).getReg()))
2523 return true;
2524
2525 // Make sure this isn't copying exec as a normal operand
2526 return MI.readsRegister(AMDGPU::EXEC, &RI);
2527 }
2528
2529 // Make a conservative assumption about the callee.
2530 if (MI.isCall())
2531 return true;
2532
2533 // Be conservative with any unhandled generic opcodes.
2534 if (!isTargetSpecificOpcode(MI.getOpcode()))
2535 return true;
2536
2537 return !isSALU(MI) || MI.readsRegister(AMDGPU::EXEC, &RI);
2538}
2539
2540bool SIInstrInfo::isInlineConstant(const APInt &Imm) const {
2541 switch (Imm.getBitWidth()) {
2542 case 1: // This likely will be a condition code mask.
2543 return true;
2544
2545 case 32:
2546 return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral32(Imm.getSExtValue(),
2547 ST.hasInv2PiInlineImm());
2548 case 64:
2549 return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral64(Imm.getSExtValue(),
2550 ST.hasInv2PiInlineImm());
2551 case 16:
2552 return ST.has16BitInsts() &&
2553 AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral16(Imm.getSExtValue(),
2554 ST.hasInv2PiInlineImm());
2555 default:
2556 llvm_unreachable("invalid bitwidth");
2557 }
2558}
2559
2560bool SIInstrInfo::isInlineConstant(const MachineOperand &MO,
2561 uint8_t OperandType) const {
2562 if (!MO.isImm() ||
2563 OperandType < AMDGPU::OPERAND_SRC_FIRST ||
2564 OperandType > AMDGPU::OPERAND_SRC_LAST)
2565 return false;
2566
2567 // MachineOperand provides no way to tell the true operand size, since it only
2568 // records a 64-bit value. We need to know the size to determine if a 32-bit
2569 // floating point immediate bit pattern is legal for an integer immediate. It
2570 // would be for any 32-bit integer operand, but would not be for a 64-bit one.
2571
2572 int64_t Imm = MO.getImm();
2573 switch (OperandType) {
2574 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT32:
2575 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP32:
2576 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT32:
2577 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP32: {
2578 int32_t Trunc = static_cast<int32_t>(Imm);
2579 return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral32(Trunc, ST.hasInv2PiInlineImm());
2580 }
2581 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT64:
2582 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP64:
2583 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT64:
2584 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP64:
2585 return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral64(MO.getImm(),
2586 ST.hasInv2PiInlineImm());
2587 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT16:
2588 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP16:
2589 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT16:
2590 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP16: {
2591 if (isInt<16>(Imm) || isUInt<16>(Imm)) {
2592 // A few special case instructions have 16-bit operands on subtargets
2593 // where 16-bit instructions are not legal.
2594 // TODO: Do the 32-bit immediates work? We shouldn't really need to handle
2595 // constants in these cases
2596 int16_t Trunc = static_cast<int16_t>(Imm);
2597 return ST.has16BitInsts() &&
2598 AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral16(Trunc, ST.hasInv2PiInlineImm());
2599 }
2600
2601 return false;
2602 }
2603 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2INT16:
2604 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2FP16:
2605 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2INT16:
2606 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2FP16: {
2607 uint32_t Trunc = static_cast<uint32_t>(Imm);
2608 return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteralV216(Trunc, ST.hasInv2PiInlineImm());
2609 }
2610 default:
2611 llvm_unreachable("invalid bitwidth");
2612 }
2613}
2614
2615bool SIInstrInfo::isLiteralConstantLike(const MachineOperand &MO,
2616 const MCOperandInfo &OpInfo) const {
2617 switch (MO.getType()) {
2618 case MachineOperand::MO_Register:
2619 return false;
2620 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate:
2621 return !isInlineConstant(MO, OpInfo);
2622 case MachineOperand::MO_FrameIndex:
2623 case MachineOperand::MO_MachineBasicBlock:
2624 case MachineOperand::MO_ExternalSymbol:
2625 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress:
2626 case MachineOperand::MO_MCSymbol:
2627 return true;
2628 default:
2629 llvm_unreachable("unexpected operand type");
2630 }
2631}
2632
2633static bool compareMachineOp(const MachineOperand &Op0,
2634 const MachineOperand &Op1) {
2635 if (Op0.getType() != Op1.getType())
2636 return false;
2637
2638 switch (Op0.getType()) {
2639 case MachineOperand::MO_Register:
2640 return Op0.getReg() == Op1.getReg();
2641 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate:
2642 return Op0.getImm() == Op1.getImm();
2643 default:
2644 llvm_unreachable("Didn't expect to be comparing these operand types");
2645 }
2646}
2647
2648bool SIInstrInfo::isImmOperandLegal(const MachineInstr &MI, unsigned OpNo,
2649 const MachineOperand &MO) const {
2650 const MCInstrDesc &InstDesc = MI.getDesc();
2651 const MCOperandInfo &OpInfo = InstDesc.OpInfo[OpNo];
2652
2653 assert(MO.isImm() || MO.isTargetIndex() || MO.isFI());
2654
2655 if (OpInfo.OperandType == MCOI::OPERAND_IMMEDIATE)
2656 return true;
2657
2658 if (OpInfo.RegClass < 0)
2659 return false;
2660
2661 if (MO.isImm() && isInlineConstant(MO, OpInfo))
2662 return RI.opCanUseInlineConstant(OpInfo.OperandType);
2663
2664 if (!RI.opCanUseLiteralConstant(OpInfo.OperandType))
2665 return false;
2666
2667 if (!isVOP3(MI) || !AMDGPU::isSISrcOperand(InstDesc, OpNo))
2668 return true;
2669
2670 const MachineFunction *MF = MI.getParent()->getParent();
2671 const GCNSubtarget &ST = MF->getSubtarget<GCNSubtarget>();
2672 return ST.hasVOP3Literal();
2673}

2700 hasModifiersSet(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src2_modifiers) ||

2704
2705bool SIInstrInfo::canShrink(const MachineInstr &MI,
2706 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) const {
2707 const MachineOperand *Src2 = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src2);
2708 // Can't shrink instruction with three operands.
2709 // FIXME: v_cndmask_b32 has 3 operands and is shrinkable, but we need to add
2710 // a special case for it. It can only be shrunk if the third operand
2711 // is vcc, and src0_modifiers and src1_modifiers are not set.
2712 // We should handle this the same way we handle vopc, by addding
2713 // a register allocation hint pre-regalloc and then do the shrinking
2714 // post-regalloc.
2715 if (Src2) {
2716 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
2717 default: return false;
2718
2719 case AMDGPU::V_ADDC_U32_e64:
2720 case AMDGPU::V_SUBB_U32_e64:
2721 case AMDGPU::V_SUBBREV_U32_e64: {
2722 const MachineOperand *Src1
2723 = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src1);
2724 if (!Src1->isReg() || !RI.isVGPR(MRI, Src1->getReg()))
2725 return false;
2726 // Additional verification is needed for sdst/src2.
2727 return true;
2728 }
2729 case AMDGPU::V_MAC_F32_e64:
2730 case AMDGPU::V_MAC_F16_e64:
2731 case AMDGPU::V_FMAC_F32_e64:
2732 case AMDGPU::V_FMAC_F16_e64:
2733 if (!Src2->isReg() || !RI.isVGPR(MRI, Src2->getReg()) ||
2734 hasModifiersSet(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src2_modifiers))
2735 return false;
2736 break;
2737
2738 case AMDGPU::V_CNDMASK_B32_e64:
2739 break;
2740 }
2741 }
2742
2743 const MachineOperand *Src1 = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src1);
2744 if (Src1 && (!Src1->isReg() || !RI.isVGPR(MRI, Src1->getReg()) ||
2745 hasModifiersSet(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src1_modifiers)))
2746 return false;
2747
2748 // We don't need to check src0, all input types are legal, so just make sure
2749 // src0 isn't using any modifiers.
2750 if (hasModifiersSet(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src0_modifiers))
2751 return false;
2752
2753 // Can it be shrunk to a valid 32 bit opcode?
2754 if (!hasVALU32BitEncoding(MI.getOpcode()))
2755 return false;
2756
2757 // Check output modifiers
2758 return !hasModifiersSet(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::omod) &&
2759 !hasModifiersSet(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::clamp);
2760}
2761
2762// Set VCC operand with all flags from \p Orig, except for setting it as
2763// implicit.
2764static void copyFlagsToImplicitVCC(MachineInstr &MI,
2765 const MachineOperand &Orig) {
2766
2767 for (MachineOperand &Use : MI.implicit_operands()) {
2768 if (Use.isUse() && Use.getReg() == AMDGPU::VCC) {
2769 Use.setIsUndef(Orig.isUndef());
2770 Use.setIsKill(Orig.isKill());
2771 return;
2772 }
2773 }
2774}
2775
2776MachineInstr *SIInstrInfo::buildShrunkInst(MachineInstr &MI,
2777 unsigned Op32) const {
2778 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI.getParent();;
2779 MachineInstrBuilder Inst32 =
2780 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(Op32));
2781
2782 // Add the dst operand if the 32-bit encoding also has an explicit $vdst.
2783 // For VOPC instructions, this is replaced by an implicit def of vcc.
2784 int Op32DstIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Op32, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst);
2785 if (Op32DstIdx != -1) {
2786 // dst
2787 Inst32.add(MI.getOperand(0));
2788 } else {
2789 assert(MI.getOperand(0).getReg() == AMDGPU::VCC &&
2790 "Unexpected case");
2791 }
2792
2793 Inst32.add(*getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src0));
2794
2795 const MachineOperand *Src1 = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src1);
2796 if (Src1)
2797 Inst32.add(*Src1);
2798
2799 const MachineOperand *Src2 = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src2);
2800
2801 if (Src2) {
2802 int Op32Src2Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Op32, AMDGPU::OpName::src2);
2803 if (Op32Src2Idx != -1) {
2804 Inst32.add(*Src2);
2805 } else {
2806 // In the case of V_CNDMASK_B32_e32, the explicit operand src2 is
2807 // replaced with an implicit read of vcc. This was already added
2808 // during the initial BuildMI, so find it to preserve the flags.
2809 copyFlagsToImplicitVCC(*Inst32, *Src2);
2810 }
2811 }
2812
2813 return Inst32;
2814}
2815
2816bool SIInstrInfo::usesConstantBus(const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
2817 const MachineOperand &MO,
2818 const MCOperandInfo &OpInfo) const {
2819 // Literal constants use the constant bus.
2820 //if (isLiteralConstantLike(MO, OpInfo))
2821 // return true;
2822 if (MO.isImm())
2823 return !isInlineConstant(MO, OpInfo);
2824
2825 if (!MO.isReg())
2826 return true; // Misc other operands like FrameIndex
2827
2828 if (!MO.isUse())
2829 return false;
2830
2831 if (TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(MO.getReg()))
2832 return RI.isSGPRClass(MRI.getRegClass(MO.getReg()));
2833
2834 // Null is free
2835 if (MO.getReg() == AMDGPU::SGPR_NULL)
2836 return false;
2837
2838 // SGPRs use the constant bus
2839 if (MO.isImplicit()) {
2840 return MO.getReg() == AMDGPU::M0 ||
2841 MO.getReg() == AMDGPU::VCC ||
2842 MO.getReg() == AMDGPU::VCC_LO;
2843 } else {
2844 return AMDGPU::SReg_32RegClass.contains(MO.getReg()) ||
2845 AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass.contains(MO.getReg());
2846 }
2847}
2848
2849static unsigned findImplicitSGPRRead(const MachineInstr &MI) {
2850 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.implicit_operands()) {
2851 // We only care about reads.
2852 if (MO.isDef())
2853 continue;
2854
2855 switch (MO.getReg()) {
2856 case AMDGPU::VCC:
2857 case AMDGPU::M0:
2858 case AMDGPU::FLAT_SCR:
2859 return MO.getReg();
2860
2861 default:
2862 break;
2863 }
2864 }
2865
2866 return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2867}

2869static bool shouldReadExec(const MachineInstr &MI) {
2870 if (SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI)) {
2871 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
2872 case AMDGPU::V_READLANE_B32:
2873 case AMDGPU::V_READLANE_B32_gfx6_gfx7:
2874 case AMDGPU::V_READLANE_B32_gfx10:
2875 case AMDGPU::V_READLANE_B32_vi:
2876 case AMDGPU::V_WRITELANE_B32:
2877 case AMDGPU::V_WRITELANE_B32_gfx6_gfx7:
2878 case AMDGPU::V_WRITELANE_B32_gfx10:

2894static bool isSubRegOf(const SIRegisterInfo &TRI,
2895 const MachineOperand &SuperVec,
2896 const MachineOperand &SubReg) {
2897 if (TargetRegisterInfo::isPhysicalRegister(SubReg.getReg()))
2898 return TRI.isSubRegister(SuperVec.getReg(), SubReg.getReg());

2901 SubReg.getReg() == SuperVec.getReg();

2903
2904bool SIInstrInfo::verifyInstruction(const MachineInstr &MI,
2905 StringRef &ErrInfo) const {
2906 uint16_t Opcode = MI.getOpcode();
2907 if (SIInstrInfo::isGenericOpcode(MI.getOpcode()))
2908 return true;
2909
2910 const MachineFunction *MF = MI.getParent()->getParent();
2911 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF->getRegInfo();
2912
2913 int Src0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::src0);
2914 int Src1Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::src1);
2915 int Src2Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::src2);
2916
2917 // Make sure the number of operands is correct.
2918 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = get(Opcode);
2919 if (!Desc.isVariadic() &&
2920 Desc.getNumOperands() != MI.getNumExplicitOperands()) {
2921 ErrInfo = "Instruction has wrong number of operands.";
2922 return false;
2923 }
2924
2925 if (MI.isInlineAsm()) {
2926 // Verify register classes for inlineasm constraints.
2927 for (unsigned I = InlineAsm::MIOp_FirstOperand, E = MI.getNumOperands();
2928 I != E; ++I) {
2929 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MI.getRegClassConstraint(I, this, &RI);
2930 if (!RC)
2931 continue;
2932
2933 const MachineOperand &Op = MI.getOperand(I);
2934 if (!Op.isReg())
2935 continue;
2936
2937 unsigned Reg = Op.getReg();
2938 if (!TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(Reg) && !RC->contains(Reg)) {
2939 ErrInfo = "inlineasm operand has incorrect register class.";
2940 return false;
2941 }
2942 }
2943
2944 return true;
2945 }
2946
2947 // Make sure the register classes are correct.
2948 for (int i = 0, e = Desc.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
2949 if (MI.getOperand(i).isFPImm()) {
2950 ErrInfo = "FPImm Machine Operands are not supported. ISel should bitcast "
2951 "all fp values to integers.";
2952 return false;
2953 }
2954
2955 int RegClass = Desc.OpInfo[i].RegClass;
2956
2957 switch (Desc.OpInfo[i].OperandType) {
2958 case MCOI::OPERAND_REGISTER:
2959 if (MI.getOperand(i).isImm()) {
2960 ErrInfo = "Illegal immediate value for operand.";
2961 return false;
2962 }
2963 break;
2964 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT32:
2965 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP32:
2966 break;
2967 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT32:
2968 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP32:
2969 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT64:
2970 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP64:
2971 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT16:
2972 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP16: {
2973 const MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(i);
2974 if (!MO.isReg() && (!MO.isImm() || !isInlineConstant(MI, i))) {
2975 ErrInfo = "Illegal immediate value for operand.";
2976 return false;
2977 }
2978 break;
2979 }
2980 case MCOI::OPERAND_IMMEDIATE:
2981 case AMDGPU::OPERAND_KIMM32:
2982 // Check if this operand is an immediate.
2983 // FrameIndex operands will be replaced by immediates, so they are
2984 // allowed.
2985 if (!MI.getOperand(i).isImm() && !MI.getOperand(i).isFI()) {
2986 ErrInfo = "Expected immediate, but got non-immediate";
2987 return false;
2988 }
2989 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2990 default:
2991 continue;
2992 }
2993
2994 if (!MI.getOperand(i).isReg())
2995 continue;
2996
2997 if (RegClass != -1) {
2998 unsigned Reg = MI.getOperand(i).getReg();
2999 if (Reg == AMDGPU::NoRegister ||
3000 TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(Reg))
3001 continue;
3002
3003 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = RI.getRegClass(RegClass);
3004 if (!RC->contains(Reg)) {
3005 ErrInfo = "Operand has incorrect register class.";
3006 return false;
3007 }
3008 }
3009 }
3010
3011 // Verify SDWA
3012 if (isSDWA(MI)) {
3013 if (!ST.hasSDWA()) {
3014 ErrInfo = "SDWA is not supported on this target";
3015 return false;
3016 }
3017
3018 int DstIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst);
3019
3020 const int OpIndicies[] = { DstIdx, Src0Idx, Src1Idx, Src2Idx };
3021
3022 for (int OpIdx: OpIndicies) {
3023 if (OpIdx == -1)
3024 continue;
3025 const MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(OpIdx);
3026
3027 if (!ST.hasSDWAScalar()) {
3028 // Only VGPRS on VI
3029 if (!MO.isReg() || !RI.hasVGPRs(RI.getRegClassForReg(MRI, MO.getReg()))) {
3030 ErrInfo = "Only VGPRs allowed as operands in SDWA instructions on VI";
3031 return false;
3032 }
3033 } else {
3034 // No immediates on GFX9
3035 if (!MO.isReg()) {
3036 ErrInfo = "Only reg allowed as operands in SDWA instructions on GFX9";
3037 return false;
3038 }
3039 }
3040 }
3041
3042 if (!ST.hasSDWAOmod()) {
3043 // No omod allowed on VI
3044 const MachineOperand *OMod = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::omod);
3045 if (OMod != nullptr &&
3046 (!OMod->isImm() || OMod->getImm() != 0)) {
3047 ErrInfo = "OMod not allowed in SDWA instructions on VI";
3048 return false;
3049 }
3050 }
3051
3052 uint16_t BasicOpcode = AMDGPU::getBasicFromSDWAOp(Opcode);
3053 if (isVOPC(BasicOpcode)) {
3054 if (!ST.hasSDWASdst() && DstIdx != -1) {
3055 // Only vcc allowed as dst on VI for VOPC
3056 const MachineOperand &Dst = MI.getOperand(DstIdx);
3057 if (!Dst.isReg() || Dst.getReg() != AMDGPU::VCC) {
3058 ErrInfo = "Only VCC allowed as dst in SDWA instructions on VI";
3059 return false;
3060 }
3061 } else if (!ST.hasSDWAOutModsVOPC()) {
3062 // No clamp allowed on GFX9 for VOPC
3063 const MachineOperand *Clamp = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::clamp);
3064 if (Clamp && (!Clamp->isImm() || Clamp->getImm() != 0)) {
3065 ErrInfo = "Clamp not allowed in VOPC SDWA instructions on VI";
3066 return false;
3067 }
3068
3069 // No omod allowed on GFX9 for VOPC
3070 const MachineOperand *OMod = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::omod);
3071 if (OMod && (!OMod->isImm() || OMod->getImm() != 0)) {
3072 ErrInfo = "OMod not allowed in VOPC SDWA instructions on VI";
3073 return false;
3074 }
3075 }
3076 }
3077
3078 const MachineOperand *DstUnused = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::dst_unused);
3079 if (DstUnused && DstUnused->isImm() &&
3080 DstUnused->getImm() == AMDGPU::SDWA::UNUSED_PRESERVE) {
3081 const MachineOperand &Dst = MI.getOperand(DstIdx);
3082 if (!Dst.isReg() || !Dst.isTied()) {
3083 ErrInfo = "Dst register should have tied register";
3084 return false;
3085 }
3086
3087 const MachineOperand &TiedMO =
3088 MI.getOperand(MI.findTiedOperandIdx(DstIdx));
3089 if (!TiedMO.isReg() || !TiedMO.isImplicit() || !TiedMO.isUse()) {
3090 ErrInfo =
3091 "Dst register should be tied to implicit use of preserved register";
3092 return false;
3093 } else if (TargetRegisterInfo::isPhysicalRegister(TiedMO.getReg()) &&
3094 Dst.getReg() != TiedMO.getReg()) {
3095 ErrInfo = "Dst register should use same physical register as preserved";
3096 return false;
3097 }
3098 }
3099 }
3100
3101 // Verify MIMG
3102 if (isMIMG(MI.getOpcode()) && !MI.mayStore()) {
3103 // Ensure that the return type used is large enough for all the options
3104 // being used TFE/LWE require an extra result register.
3105 const MachineOperand *DMask = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::dmask);
3106 if (DMask) {
3107 uint64_t DMaskImm = DMask->getImm();
3108 uint32_t RegCount =
3109 isGather4(MI.getOpcode()) ? 4 : countPopulation(DMaskImm);
3110 const MachineOperand *TFE = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::tfe);
3111 const MachineOperand *LWE = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::lwe);
3112 const MachineOperand *D16 = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::d16);
3113
3114 // Adjust for packed 16 bit values
3115 if (D16 && D16->getImm() && !ST.hasUnpackedD16VMem())
3116 RegCount >>= 1;
3117
3118 // Adjust if using LWE or TFE
3119 if ((LWE && LWE->getImm()) || (TFE && TFE->getImm()))
3120 RegCount += 1;
3121
3122 const uint32_t DstIdx =
3123 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(MI.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::vdata);
3124 const MachineOperand &Dst = MI.getOperand(DstIdx);
3125 if (Dst.isReg()) {
3126 const TargetRegisterClass *DstRC = getOpRegClass(MI, DstIdx);
3127 uint32_t DstSize = RI.getRegSizeInBits(*DstRC) / 32;
3128 if (RegCount > DstSize) {
3129 ErrInfo = "MIMG instruction returns too many registers for dst "
3130 "register class";
3131 return false;
3132 }
3133 }
3134 }
3135 }
3136
3137 // Verify VOP*. Ignore multiple sgpr operands on writelane.
3138 if (Desc.getOpcode() != AMDGPU::V_WRITELANE_B32
3139 && (isVOP1(MI) || isVOP2(MI) || isVOP3(MI) || isVOPC(MI) || isSDWA(MI))) {
3140 // Only look at the true operands. Only a real operand can use the constant
3141 // bus, and we don't want to check pseudo-operands like the source modifier
3142 // flags.
3143 const int OpIndices[] = { Src0Idx, Src1Idx, Src2Idx };
3144
3145 unsigned ConstantBusCount = 0;
3146 unsigned LiteralCount = 0;
3147
3148 if (AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::imm) != -1)
3149 ++ConstantBusCount;
3150
3151 SmallVector<unsigned, 2> SGPRsUsed;
3152 unsigned SGPRUsed = findImplicitSGPRRead(MI);
3153 if (SGPRUsed != AMDGPU::NoRegister) {
3154 ++ConstantBusCount;
3155 SGPRsUsed.push_back(SGPRUsed);
3156 }
3157
3158 for (int OpIdx : OpIndices) {
3159 if (OpIdx == -1)
3160 break;
3161 const MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(OpIdx);
3162 if (usesConstantBus(MRI, MO, MI.getDesc().OpInfo[OpIdx])) {
3163 if (MO.isReg()) {
3164 SGPRUsed = MO.getReg();
3165 if (llvm::all_of(SGPRsUsed, [this, SGPRUsed](unsigned SGPR) {
3166 return !RI.regsOverlap(SGPRUsed, SGPR);
3167 })) {
3168 ++ConstantBusCount;
3169 SGPRsUsed.push_back(SGPRUsed);
3170 }
3171 } else {
3172 ++ConstantBusCount;
3173 ++LiteralCount;
3174 }
3175 }
3176 }
3177 const GCNSubtarget &ST = MF->getSubtarget<GCNSubtarget>();
3178 // v_writelane_b32 is an exception from constant bus restriction:
3179 // vsrc0 can be sgpr, const or m0 and lane select sgpr, m0 or inline-const
3180 if (ConstantBusCount > ST.getConstantBusLimit(Opcode) &&
3181 Opcode != AMDGPU::V_WRITELANE_B32) {
3182 ErrInfo = "VOP* instruction violates constant bus restriction";
3183 return false;
3184 }
3185
3186 if (isVOP3(MI) && LiteralCount) {
3187 if (LiteralCount && !ST.hasVOP3Literal()) {
3188 ErrInfo = "VOP3 instruction uses literal";
3189 return false;
3190 }
3191 if (LiteralCount > 1) {
3192 ErrInfo = "VOP3 instruction uses more than one literal";
3193 return false;
3194 }
3195 }
3196 }
3197
3198 // Verify misc. restrictions on specific instructions.
3199 if (Desc.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_DIV_SCALE_F32 ||
3200 Desc.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_DIV_SCALE_F64) {
3201 const MachineOperand &Src0 = MI.getOperand(Src0Idx);
3202 const MachineOperand &Src1 = MI.getOperand(Src1Idx);
3203 const MachineOperand &Src2 = MI.getOperand(Src2Idx);
3204 if (Src0.isReg() && Src1.isReg() && Src2.isReg()) {
3205 if (!compareMachineOp(Src0, Src1) &&
3206 !compareMachineOp(Src0, Src2)) {
3207 ErrInfo = "v_div_scale_{f32|f64} require src0 = src1 or src2";
3208 return false;
3209 }
3210 }
3211 }
3212
3213 if (isSOP2(MI) || isSOPC(MI)) {
3214 const MachineOperand &Src0 = MI.getOperand(Src0Idx);
3215 const MachineOperand &Src1 = MI.getOperand(Src1Idx);
3216 unsigned Immediates = 0;
3217
3218 if (!Src0.isReg() &&
3219 !isInlineConstant(Src0, Desc.OpInfo[Src0Idx].OperandType))
3220 Immediates++;
3221 if (!Src1.isReg() &&
3222 !isInlineConstant(Src1, Desc.OpInfo[Src1Idx].OperandType))
3223 Immediates++;
3224
3225 if (Immediates > 1) {
3226 ErrInfo = "SOP2/SOPC instruction requires too many immediate constants";
3227 return false;
3228 }
3229 }
3230
3231 if (isSOPK(MI)) {
3232 auto Op = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::simm16);
3233 if (Desc.isBranch()) {
3234 if (!Op->isMBB()) {
3235 ErrInfo = "invalid branch target for SOPK instruction";
3236 return false;
3237 }
3238 } else {
3239 uint64_t Imm = Op->getImm();
3240 if (sopkIsZext(MI)) {
3241 if (!isUInt<16>(Imm)) {
3242 ErrInfo = "invalid immediate for SOPK instruction";
3243 return false;
3244 }
3245 } else {
3246 if (!isInt<16>(Imm)) {
3247 ErrInfo = "invalid immediate for SOPK instruction";
3248 return false;
3249 }
3250 }
3251 }
3252 }
3253
3254 if (Desc.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_MOVRELS_B32_e32 ||
3255 Desc.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_MOVRELS_B32_e64 ||
3256 Desc.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_MOVRELD_B32_e32 ||
3257 Desc.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_MOVRELD_B32_e64) {
3258 const bool IsDst = Desc.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_MOVRELD_B32_e32 ||
3259 Desc.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_MOVRELD_B32_e64;
3260
3261 const unsigned StaticNumOps = Desc.getNumOperands() +
3262 Desc.getNumImplicitUses();
3263 const unsigned NumImplicitOps = IsDst ? 2 : 1;
3264
3265 // Allow additional implicit operands. This allows a fixup done by the post
3266 // RA scheduler where the main implicit operand is killed and implicit-defs
3267 // are added for sub-registers that remain live after this instruction.
3268 if (MI.getNumOperands() < StaticNumOps + NumImplicitOps) {
3269 ErrInfo = "missing implicit register operands";
3270 return false;
3271 }
3272
3273 const MachineOperand *Dst = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst);
3274 if (IsDst) {
3275 if (!Dst->isUse()) {
3276 ErrInfo = "v_movreld_b32 vdst should be a use operand";
3277 return false;
3278 }
3279
3280 unsigned UseOpIdx;
3281 if (!MI.isRegTiedToUseOperand(StaticNumOps, &UseOpIdx) ||
3282 UseOpIdx != StaticNumOps + 1) {
3283 ErrInfo = "movrel implicit operands should be tied";
3284 return false;
3285 }
3286 }
3287
3288 const MachineOperand &Src0 = MI.getOperand(Src0Idx);
3289 const MachineOperand &ImpUse
3290 = MI.getOperand(StaticNumOps + NumImplicitOps - 1);
3291 if (!ImpUse.isReg() || !ImpUse.isUse() ||
3292 !isSubRegOf(RI, ImpUse, IsDst ? *Dst : Src0)) {
3293 ErrInfo = "src0 should be subreg of implicit vector use";
3294 return false;
3295 }
3296 }
3297
3298 // Make sure we aren't losing exec uses in the td files. This mostly requires
3299 // being careful when using let Uses to try to add other use registers.
3300 if (shouldReadExec(MI)) {
3301 if (!MI.hasRegisterImplicitUseOperand(AMDGPU::EXEC)) {
3302 ErrInfo = "VALU instruction does not implicitly read exec mask";
3303 return false;
3304 }
3305 }
3306
3307 if (isSMRD(MI)) {
3308 if (MI.mayStore()) {
3309 // The register offset form of scalar stores may only use m0 as the
3310 // soffset register.
3311 const MachineOperand *Soff = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::soff);
3312 if (Soff && Soff->getReg() != AMDGPU::M0) {
3313 ErrInfo = "scalar stores must use m0 as offset register";
3314 return false;
3315 }
3316 }
3317 }
3318
3319 if (isFLAT(MI) && !MF->getSubtarget<GCNSubtarget>().hasFlatInstOffsets()) {
3320 const MachineOperand *Offset = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::offset);
3321 if (Offset->getImm() != 0) {
3322 ErrInfo = "subtarget does not support offsets in flat instructions";
3323 return false;
3324 }
3325 }
3326
3327 if (isMIMG(MI)) {
3328 const MachineOperand *DimOp = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::dim);
3329 if (DimOp) {
3330 int VAddr0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode,
3331 AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr0);
3332 int SRsrcIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::srsrc);
3333 const AMDGPU::MIMGInfo *Info = AMDGPU::getMIMGInfo(Opcode);
3334 const AMDGPU::MIMGBaseOpcodeInfo *BaseOpcode =
3335 AMDGPU::getMIMGBaseOpcodeInfo(Info->BaseOpcode);
3336 const AMDGPU::MIMGDimInfo *Dim =
3337 AMDGPU::getMIMGDimInfoByEncoding(DimOp->getImm());
3338
3339 if (!Dim) {
3340 ErrInfo = "dim is out of range";
3341 return false;
3342 }
3343
3344 bool IsNSA = SRsrcIdx - VAddr0Idx > 1;
3345 unsigned AddrWords = BaseOpcode->NumExtraArgs +
3346 (BaseOpcode->Gradients ? Dim->NumGradients : 0) +
3347 (BaseOpcode->Coordinates ? Dim->NumCoords : 0) +
3348 (BaseOpcode->LodOrClampOrMip ? 1 : 0);
3349
3350 unsigned VAddrWords;
3351 if (IsNSA) {
3352 VAddrWords = SRsrcIdx - VAddr0Idx;
3353 } else {
3354 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getOpRegClass(MI, VAddr0Idx);
3355 VAddrWords = MRI.getTargetRegisterInfo()->getRegSizeInBits(*RC) / 32;
3356 if (AddrWords > 8)
3357 AddrWords = 16;
3358 else if (AddrWords > 4)
3359 AddrWords = 8;
3360 else if (AddrWords == 3 && VAddrWords == 4) {
3361 // CodeGen uses the V4 variant of instructions for three addresses,
3362 // because the selection DAG does not support non-power-of-two types.
3363 AddrWords = 4;
3364 }
3365 }
3366
3367 if (VAddrWords != AddrWords) {
3368 ErrInfo = "bad vaddr size";
3369 return false;
3370 }
3371 }
3372 }
3373
3374 const MachineOperand *DppCt = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::dpp_ctrl);
3375 if (DppCt) {
3376 using namespace AMDGPU::DPP;
3377
3378 unsigned DC = DppCt->getImm();
3379 if (DC == DppCtrl::DPP_UNUSED1 || DC == DppCtrl::DPP_UNUSED2 ||
3380 DC == DppCtrl::DPP_UNUSED3 || DC > DppCtrl::DPP_LAST ||
3381 (DC >= DppCtrl::DPP_UNUSED4_FIRST && DC <= DppCtrl::DPP_UNUSED4_LAST) ||
3382 (DC >= DppCtrl::DPP_UNUSED5_FIRST && DC <= DppCtrl::DPP_UNUSED5_LAST) ||
3383 (DC >= DppCtrl::DPP_UNUSED6_FIRST && DC <= DppCtrl::DPP_UNUSED6_LAST) ||
3384 (DC >= DppCtrl::DPP_UNUSED7_FIRST && DC <= DppCtrl::DPP_UNUSED7_LAST) ||
3385 (DC >= DppCtrl::DPP_UNUSED8_FIRST && DC <= DppCtrl::DPP_UNUSED8_LAST)) {
3386 ErrInfo = "Invalid dpp_ctrl value";
3387 return false;
3388 }
3389 if (DC >= DppCtrl::WAVE_SHL1 && DC <= DppCtrl::WAVE_ROR1 &&
3390 ST.getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX10) {
3391 ErrInfo = "Invalid dpp_ctrl value: "
3392 "wavefront shifts are not supported on GFX10+";
3393 return false;
3394 }
3395 if (DC >= DppCtrl::BCAST15 && DC <= DppCtrl::BCAST31 &&
3396 ST.getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX10) {
3397 ErrInfo = "Invalid dpp_ctrl value: "
3398 "broadcats are not supported on GFX10+";
3399 return false;
3400 }
3401 if (DC >= DppCtrl::ROW_SHARE_FIRST && DC <= DppCtrl::ROW_XMASK_LAST &&
3402 ST.getGeneration() < AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX10) {
3403 ErrInfo = "Invalid dpp_ctrl value: "
3404 "row_share and row_xmask are not supported before GFX10";
3405 return false;
3406 }
3407 }
3408
3409 return true;
3410}

3412unsigned SIInstrInfo::getVALUOp(const MachineInstr &MI) const {
3413 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
3414 default: return AMDGPU::INSTRUCTION_LIST_END;

3417 case AMDGPU::PHI: return AMDGPU::PHI;

3456 case AMDGPU::S_SEXT_I32_I16: return AMDGPU::V_BFE_I32;
3457 case AMDGPU::S_BFE_U32: return AMDGPU::V_BFE_U32;

3488const TargetRegisterClass *SIInstrInfo::getOpRegClass(const MachineInstr &MI,
3489 unsigned OpNo) const {
3490 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MI.getParent()->getParent()->getRegInfo();
3491 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = get(MI.getOpcode());
3492 if (MI.isVariadic() || OpNo >= Desc.getNumOperands() ||
3493 Desc.OpInfo[OpNo].RegClass == -1) {
3494 unsigned Reg = MI.getOperand(OpNo).getReg();
3495
3496 if (TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(Reg))
3497 return MRI.getRegClass(Reg);
3498 return RI.getPhysRegClass(Reg);
3499 }
3500
3501 unsigned RCID = Desc.OpInfo[OpNo].RegClass;
3502 return RI.getRegClass(RCID);

3504
3505void SIInstrInfo::legalizeOpWithMove(MachineInstr &MI, unsigned OpIdx) const {
3506 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = MI;
3507 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI.getParent();
3508 MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(OpIdx);
3509 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MBB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
3510 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI =
3511 static_cast<const SIRegisterInfo*>(MRI.getTargetRegisterInfo());
3512 unsigned RCID = get(MI.getOpcode()).OpInfo[OpIdx].RegClass;
3513 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = RI.getRegClass(RCID);
3514 unsigned Size = TRI->getRegSizeInBits(*RC);
3515 unsigned Opcode = (Size == 64) ? AMDGPU::V_MOV_B64_PSEUDO : AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32;
3516 if (MO.isReg())
3517 Opcode = AMDGPU::COPY;
3518 else if (RI.isSGPRClass(RC))
3519 Opcode = (Size == 64) ? AMDGPU::S_MOV_B64 : AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32;
3520
3521 const TargetRegisterClass *VRC = RI.getEquivalentVGPRClass(RC);
3522 if (RI.getCommonSubClass(&AMDGPU::VReg_64RegClass, VRC))
3523 VRC = &AMDGPU::VReg_64RegClass;
3524 else
3525 VRC = &AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass;
3526
3527 unsigned Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(VRC);
3528 DebugLoc DL = MBB->findDebugLoc(I);
3529 BuildMI(*MI.getParent(), I, DL, get(Opcode), Reg).add(MO);
3530 MO.ChangeToRegister(Reg, false);
3531}
3532
3533unsigned SIInstrInfo::buildExtractSubReg(MachineBasicBlock::iterator MI,
3534 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
3535 MachineOperand &SuperReg,
3536 const TargetRegisterClass *SuperRC,
3537 unsigned SubIdx,
3538 const TargetRegisterClass *SubRC)
3539 const {
3540 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI->getParent();
3541 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc();
3542 unsigned SubReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(SubRC);
3543
3544 if (SuperReg.getSubReg() == AMDGPU::NoSubRegister) {
3545 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, get(TargetOpcode::COPY), SubReg)
3546 .addReg(SuperReg.getReg(), 0, SubIdx);
3547 return SubReg;
3548 }
3549
3550 // Just in case the super register is itself a sub-register, copy it to a new
3551 // value so we don't need to worry about merging its subreg index with the
3552 // SubIdx passed to this function. The register coalescer should be able to
3553 // eliminate this extra copy.
3554 unsigned NewSuperReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(SuperRC);
3555
3556 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, get(TargetOpcode::COPY), NewSuperReg)
3557 .addReg(SuperReg.getReg(), 0, SuperReg.getSubReg());
3558
3559 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, get(TargetOpcode::COPY), SubReg)
3560 .addReg(NewSuperReg, 0, SubIdx);
3561
3562 return SubReg;
3563}
3564
3565MachineOperand SIInstrInfo::buildExtractSubRegOrImm(
3566 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MII,
3567 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
3568 MachineOperand &Op,
3569 const TargetRegisterClass *SuperRC,
3570 unsigned SubIdx,
3571 const TargetRegisterClass *SubRC) const {
3572 if (Op.isImm()) {
3573 if (SubIdx == AMDGPU::sub0)
3574 return MachineOperand::CreateImm(static_cast<int32_t>(Op.getImm()));
3575 if (SubIdx == AMDGPU::sub1)
3576 return MachineOperand::CreateImm(static_cast<int32_t>(Op.getImm() >> 32));
3577
3578 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled register index for immediate");
3579 }
3580
3581 unsigned SubReg = buildExtractSubReg(MII, MRI, Op, SuperRC,
3582 SubIdx, SubRC);
3583 return MachineOperand::CreateReg(SubReg, false);
3584}
3585
3586// Change the order of operands from (0, 1, 2) to (0, 2, 1)
3587void SIInstrInfo::swapOperands(MachineInstr &Inst) const {
3588 assert(Inst.getNumExplicitOperands() == 3);
3589 MachineOperand Op1 = Inst.getOperand(1);
3590 Inst.RemoveOperand(1);
3591 Inst.addOperand(Op1);
3592}
3593
3594bool SIInstrInfo::isLegalRegOperand(const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
3595 const MCOperandInfo &OpInfo,
3596 const MachineOperand &MO) const {
3597 if (!MO.isReg())
3598 return false;
3599
3600 unsigned Reg = MO.getReg();
3601 const TargetRegisterClass *RC =
3602 TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(Reg) ?
3603 MRI.getRegClass(Reg) :
3604 RI.getPhysRegClass(Reg);
3605
3606 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI =
3607 static_cast<const SIRegisterInfo*>(MRI.getTargetRegisterInfo());
3608 RC = TRI->getSubRegClass(RC, MO.getSubReg());
3609
3610 // In order to be legal, the common sub-class must be equal to the
3611 // class of the current operand. For example:
3612 //
3613 // v_mov_b32 s0 ; Operand defined as vsrc_b32
3614 // ; RI.getCommonSubClass(s0,vsrc_b32) = sgpr ; LEGAL
3615 //
3616 // s_sendmsg 0, s0 ; Operand defined as m0reg
3617 // ; RI.getCommonSubClass(s0,m0reg) = m0reg ; NOT LEGAL
3618
3619 return RI.getCommonSubClass(RC, RI.getRegClass(OpInfo.RegClass)) == RC;
3620}
3621
3622bool SIInstrInfo::isLegalVSrcOperand(const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
3623 const MCOperandInfo &OpInfo,
3624 const MachineOperand &MO) const {
3625 if (MO.isReg())
3626 return isLegalRegOperand(MRI, OpInfo, MO);
3627
3628 // Handle non-register types that are treated like immediates.
3629 assert(MO.isImm() || MO.isTargetIndex() || MO.isFI());
3630 return true;
3631}
3632
3633bool SIInstrInfo::isOperandLegal(const MachineInstr &MI, unsigned OpIdx,
3634 const MachineOperand *MO) const {
3635 const MachineFunction &MF = *MI.getParent()->getParent();
3636 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
3637 const MCInstrDesc &InstDesc = MI.getDesc();
3638 const MCOperandInfo &OpInfo = InstDesc.OpInfo[OpIdx];
3639 const GCNSubtarget &ST = MF.getSubtarget<GCNSubtarget>();
3640 const TargetRegisterClass *DefinedRC =
3641 OpInfo.RegClass != -1 ? RI.getRegClass(OpInfo.RegClass) : nullptr;
3642 if (!MO)
3643 MO = &MI.getOperand(OpIdx);
3644
3645 int ConstantBusLimit = ST.getConstantBusLimit(MI.getOpcode());
3646 int VOP3LiteralLimit = ST.hasVOP3Literal() ? 1 : 0;
3647 if (isVALU(MI) && usesConstantBus(MRI, *MO, OpInfo)) {
3648 if (isVOP3(MI) && isLiteralConstantLike(*MO, OpInfo) && !VOP3LiteralLimit--)
3649 return false;
3650
3651 SmallDenseSet<RegSubRegPair> SGPRsUsed;
3652 if (MO->isReg())
3653 SGPRsUsed.insert(RegSubRegPair(MO->getReg(), MO->getSubReg()));
3654
3655 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MI.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
3656 if (i == OpIdx)
3657 continue;
3658 const MachineOperand &Op = MI.getOperand(i);
3659 if (Op.isReg()) {
3660 RegSubRegPair SGPR(Op.getReg(), Op.getSubReg());
3661 if (!SGPRsUsed.count(SGPR) &&
3662 usesConstantBus(MRI, Op, InstDesc.OpInfo[i])) {
3663 if (--ConstantBusLimit <= 0)
3664 return false;
3665 SGPRsUsed.insert(SGPR);
3666 }
3667 } else if (InstDesc.OpInfo[i].OperandType == AMDGPU::OPERAND_KIMM32) {
3668 if (--ConstantBusLimit <= 0)
3669 return false;
3670 } else if (isVOP3(MI) && AMDGPU::isSISrcOperand(InstDesc, i) &&
3671 isLiteralConstantLike(Op, InstDesc.OpInfo[i])) {
3672 if (!VOP3LiteralLimit--)
3673 return false;
3674 if (--ConstantBusLimit <= 0)
3675 return false;
3676 }
3677 }
3678 }
3679
3680 if (MO->isReg()) {
3681 assert(DefinedRC);
3682 return isLegalRegOperand(MRI, OpInfo, *MO);
3683 }
3684
3685 // Handle non-register types that are treated like immediates.
3686 assert(MO->isImm() || MO->isTargetIndex() || MO->isFI());
3687
3688 if (!DefinedRC) {
3689 // This operand expects an immediate.
3690 return true;
3691 }
3692
3693 return isImmOperandLegal(MI, OpIdx, *MO);
3694}
3695
3696void SIInstrInfo::legalizeOperandsVOP2(MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
3697 MachineInstr &MI) const {
3698 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode();
3699 const MCInstrDesc &InstrDesc = get(Opc);
3700
3701 int Src1Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src1);
3702 MachineOperand &Src1 = MI.getOperand(Src1Idx);
3703
3704 // If there is an implicit SGPR use such as VCC use for v_addc_u32/v_subb_u32
3705 // we need to only have one constant bus use before GFX10.
3706 bool HasImplicitSGPR = findImplicitSGPRRead(MI) != AMDGPU::NoRegister;
3707 if (HasImplicitSGPR && ST.getConstantBusLimit(Opc) <= 1) {
3708 int Src0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src0);
3709 MachineOperand &Src0 = MI.getOperand(Src0Idx);
3710
3711 if (Src0.isReg() && (RI.isSGPRReg(MRI, Src0.getReg()) ||
3712 isLiteralConstantLike(Src0, InstrDesc.OpInfo[Src0Idx])))
3713 legalizeOpWithMove(MI, Src0Idx);
3714 }
3715
3716 // Special case: V_WRITELANE_B32 accepts only immediate or SGPR operands for
3717 // both the value to write (src0) and lane select (src1). Fix up non-SGPR
3718 // src0/src1 with V_READFIRSTLANE.
3719 if (Opc == AMDGPU::V_WRITELANE_B32) {
3720 int Src0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src0);
3721 MachineOperand &Src0 = MI.getOperand(Src0Idx);
3722 const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3723 if (Src0.isReg() && RI.isVGPR(MRI, Src0.getReg())) {
3724 unsigned Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_32_XM0RegClass);
3725 BuildMI(*MI.getParent(), MI, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32), Reg)
3726 .add(Src0);
3727 Src0.ChangeToRegister(Reg, false);
3728 }
3729 if (Src1.isReg() && RI.isVGPR(MRI, Src1.getReg())) {
3730 unsigned Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_32_XM0RegClass);
3731 const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3732 BuildMI(*MI.getParent(), MI, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32), Reg)
3733 .add(Src1);
3734 Src1.ChangeToRegister(Reg, false);
3735 }
3736 return;
3737 }
3738
3739 // VOP2 src0 instructions support all operand types, so we don't need to check
3740 // their legality. If src1 is already legal, we don't need to do anything.
3741 if (isLegalRegOperand(MRI, InstrDesc.OpInfo[Src1Idx], Src1))
3742 return;
3743
3744 // Special case: V_READLANE_B32 accepts only immediate or SGPR operands for
3745 // lane select. Fix up using V_READFIRSTLANE, since we assume that the lane
3746 // select is uniform.
3747 if (Opc == AMDGPU::V_READLANE_B32 && Src1.isReg() &&
3748 RI.isVGPR(MRI, Src1.getReg())) {
3749 unsigned Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_32_XM0RegClass);
3750 const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3751 BuildMI(*MI.getParent(), MI, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32), Reg)
3752 .add(Src1);
3753 Src1.ChangeToRegister(Reg, false);
3754 return;
3755 }
3756
3757 // We do not use commuteInstruction here because it is too aggressive and will
3758 // commute if it is possible. We only want to commute here if it improves
3759 // legality. This can be called a fairly large number of times so don't waste
3760 // compile time pointlessly swapping and checking legality again.
3761 if (HasImplicitSGPR || !MI.isCommutable()) {
3762 legalizeOpWithMove(MI, Src1Idx);
3763 return;
3764 }
3765
3766 int Src0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src0);
3767 MachineOperand &Src0 = MI.getOperand(Src0Idx);
3768
3769 // If src0 can be used as src1, commuting will make the operands legal.
3770 // Otherwise we have to give up and insert a move.
3771 //
3772 // TODO: Other immediate-like operand kinds could be commuted if there was a
3773 // MachineOperand::ChangeTo* for them.
3774 if ((!Src1.isImm() && !Src1.isReg()) ||
3775 !isLegalRegOperand(MRI, InstrDesc.OpInfo[Src1Idx], Src0)) {
3776 legalizeOpWithMove(MI, Src1Idx);
3777 return;
3778 }
3779
3780 int CommutedOpc = commuteOpcode(MI);
3781 if (CommutedOpc == -1) {
3782 legalizeOpWithMove(MI, Src1Idx);
3783 return;
3784 }
3785
3786 MI.setDesc(get(CommutedOpc));
3787
3788 unsigned Src0Reg = Src0.getReg();
3789 unsigned Src0SubReg = Src0.getSubReg();
3790 bool Src0Kill = Src0.isKill();
3791
3792 if (Src1.isImm())
3793 Src0.ChangeToImmediate(Src1.getImm());
3794 else if (Src1.isReg()) {
3795 Src0.ChangeToRegister(Src1.getReg(), false, false, Src1.isKill());
3796 Src0.setSubReg(Src1.getSubReg());
3797 } else
3798 llvm_unreachable("Should only have register or immediate operands");
3799
3800 Src1.ChangeToRegister(Src0Reg, false, false, Src0Kill);
3801 Src1.setSubReg(Src0SubReg);
3802}
3803
3804// Legalize VOP3 operands. All operand types are supported for any operand
3805// but only one literal constant and only starting from GFX10.
3806void SIInstrInfo::legalizeOperandsVOP3(MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
3807 MachineInstr &MI) const {
3808 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode();
3809
3810 int VOP3Idx[3] = {
3811 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src0),
3812 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src1),
3813 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src2)
3814 };
3815
3816 if (Opc == AMDGPU::V_PERMLANE16_B32 ||
3817 Opc == AMDGPU::V_PERMLANEX16_B32) {
3818 // src1 and src2 must be scalar
3819 MachineOperand &Src1 = MI.getOperand(VOP3Idx[1]);
3820 MachineOperand &Src2 = MI.getOperand(VOP3Idx[2]);
3821 const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3822 if (Src1.isReg() && !RI.isSGPRClass(MRI.getRegClass(Src1.getReg()))) {
3823 unsigned Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_32_XM0RegClass);
3824 BuildMI(*MI.getParent(), MI, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32), Reg)
3825 .add(Src1);
3826 Src1.ChangeToRegister(Reg, false);
3827 }
3828 if (Src2.isReg() && !RI.isSGPRClass(MRI.getRegClass(Src2.getReg()))) {
3829 unsigned Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_32_XM0RegClass);
3830 BuildMI(*MI.getParent(), MI, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32), Reg)
3831 .add(Src2);
3832 Src2.ChangeToRegister(Reg, false);
3833 }
3834 }
3835
3836 // Find the one SGPR operand we are allowed to use.
3837 int ConstantBusLimit = ST.getConstantBusLimit(Opc);
3838 int LiteralLimit = ST.hasVOP3Literal() ? 1 : 0;
3839 SmallDenseSet<unsigned> SGPRsUsed;
3840 unsigned SGPRReg = findUsedSGPR(MI, VOP3Idx);
3841 if (SGPRReg != AMDGPU::NoRegister) {
3842 SGPRsUsed.insert(SGPRReg);
3843 --ConstantBusLimit;
3844 }
3845
3846 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 3; ++i) {
3847 int Idx = VOP3Idx[i];
3848 if (Idx == -1)
3849 break;
3850 MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(Idx);
3851
3852 if (!MO.isReg()) {
3853 if (!isLiteralConstantLike(MO, get(Opc).OpInfo[Idx]))
3854 continue;
3855
3856 if (LiteralLimit > 0 && ConstantBusLimit > 0) {
3857 --LiteralLimit;
3858 --ConstantBusLimit;
3859 continue;
3860 }
3861
3862 --LiteralLimit;
3863 --ConstantBusLimit;
3864 legalizeOpWithMove(MI, Idx);
3865 continue;
3866 }
3867
3868 if (!RI.isSGPRClass(MRI.getRegClass(MO.getReg())))
3869 continue; // VGPRs are legal
3870
3871 // We can use one SGPR in each VOP3 instruction prior to GFX10
3872 // and two starting from GFX10.
3873 if (SGPRsUsed.count(MO.getReg()))
3874 continue;
3875 if (ConstantBusLimit > 0) {
3876 SGPRsUsed.insert(MO.getReg());
3877 --ConstantBusLimit;
3878 continue;
3879 }
3880
3881 // If we make it this far, then the operand is not legal and we must
3882 // legalize it.
3883 legalizeOpWithMove(MI, Idx);
3884 }
3885}
3886
3887unsigned SIInstrInfo::readlaneVGPRToSGPR(unsigned SrcReg, MachineInstr &UseMI,
3888 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) const {
3889 const TargetRegisterClass *VRC = MRI.getRegClass(SrcReg);
3890 const TargetRegisterClass *SRC = RI.getEquivalentSGPRClass(VRC);
3891 unsigned DstReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(SRC);
3892 unsigned SubRegs = RI.getRegSizeInBits(*VRC) / 32;
3893
3894 if (SubRegs == 1) {
3895 BuildMI(*UseMI.getParent(), UseMI, UseMI.getDebugLoc(),
3896 get(AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32), DstReg)
3897 .addReg(SrcReg);
3898 return DstReg;
3899 }
3900
3901 SmallVector<unsigned, 8> SRegs;
3902 for (unsigned i = 0; i < SubRegs; ++i) {
3903 unsigned SGPR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass);
3904 BuildMI(*UseMI.getParent(), UseMI, UseMI.getDebugLoc(),
3905 get(AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32), SGPR)
3906 .addReg(SrcReg, 0, RI.getSubRegFromChannel(i));
3907 SRegs.push_back(SGPR);
3908 }
3909
3910 MachineInstrBuilder MIB =
3911 BuildMI(*UseMI.getParent(), UseMI, UseMI.getDebugLoc(),
3912 get(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE), DstReg);
3913 for (unsigned i = 0; i < SubRegs; ++i) {
3914 MIB.addReg(SRegs[i]);
3915 MIB.addImm(RI.getSubRegFromChannel(i));
3916 }
3917 return DstReg;
3918}
3919
3920void SIInstrInfo::legalizeOperandsSMRD(MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
3921 MachineInstr &MI) const {
3922
3923 // If the pointer is store in VGPRs, then we need to move them to
3924 // SGPRs using v_readfirstlane. This is safe because we only select
3925 // loads with uniform pointers to SMRD instruction so we know the
3926 // pointer value is uniform.
3927 MachineOperand *SBase = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::sbase);
3928 if (SBase && !RI.isSGPRClass(MRI.getRegClass(SBase->getReg()))) {
3929 unsigned SGPR = readlaneVGPRToSGPR(SBase->getReg(), MI, MRI);
3930 SBase->setReg(SGPR);
3931 }
3932 MachineOperand *SOff = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::soff);
3933 if (SOff && !RI.isSGPRClass(MRI.getRegClass(SOff->getReg()))) {
3934 unsigned SGPR = readlaneVGPRToSGPR(SOff->getReg(), MI, MRI);
3935 SOff->setReg(SGPR);
3936 }
3937}
3938
3939void SIInstrInfo::legalizeGenericOperand(MachineBasicBlock &InsertMBB,
3940 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I,
3941 const TargetRegisterClass *DstRC,
3942 MachineOperand &Op,
3943 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
3944 const DebugLoc &DL) const {
3945 unsigned OpReg = Op.getReg();
3946 unsigned OpSubReg = Op.getSubReg();
3947
3948 const TargetRegisterClass *OpRC = RI.getSubClassWithSubReg(
3949 RI.getRegClassForReg(MRI, OpReg), OpSubReg);
3950
3951 // Check if operand is already the correct register class.
3952 if (DstRC == OpRC)
3953 return;
3954
3955 unsigned DstReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(DstRC);
3956 MachineInstr *Copy =
3957 BuildMI(InsertMBB, I, DL, get(AMDGPU::COPY), DstReg).add(Op);
3958
3959 Op.setReg(DstReg);
3960 Op.setSubReg(0);
3961
3962 MachineInstr *Def = MRI.getVRegDef(OpReg);
3963 if (!Def)
3964 return;
3965
3966 // Try to eliminate the copy if it is copying an immediate value.
3967 if (Def->isMoveImmediate())
3968 FoldImmediate(*Copy, *Def, OpReg, &MRI);
3969}
3970
3971// Emit the actual waterfall loop, executing the wrapped instruction for each
3972// unique value of \p Rsrc across all lanes. In the best case we execute 1
3973// iteration, in the worst case we execute 64 (once per lane).
3974static void
3975emitLoadSRsrcFromVGPRLoop(const SIInstrInfo &TII, MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
3976 MachineBasicBlock &OrigBB, MachineBasicBlock &LoopBB,
3977 const DebugLoc &DL, MachineOperand &Rsrc) {
3978 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = LoopBB.begin();
3979
3980 unsigned VRsrc = Rsrc.getReg();
3981 unsigned VRsrcUndef = getUndefRegState(Rsrc.isUndef());
3982
3983 unsigned SaveExec = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass);
3984 unsigned CondReg0 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass);
3985 unsigned CondReg1 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass);
3986 unsigned AndCond = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass);
3987 unsigned SRsrcSub0 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass);
3988 unsigned SRsrcSub1 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass);
3989 unsigned SRsrcSub2 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass);
3990 unsigned SRsrcSub3 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass);
3991 unsigned SRsrc = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_128RegClass);
3992
3993 // Beginning of the loop, read the next Rsrc variant.
3994 BuildMI(LoopBB, I, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32), SRsrcSub0)
3995 .addReg(VRsrc, VRsrcUndef, AMDGPU::sub0);
3996 BuildMI(LoopBB, I, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32), SRsrcSub1)
3997 .addReg(VRsrc, VRsrcUndef, AMDGPU::sub1);
3998 BuildMI(LoopBB, I, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32), SRsrcSub2)
3999 .addReg(VRsrc, VRsrcUndef, AMDGPU::sub2);
4000 BuildMI(LoopBB, I, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32), SRsrcSub3)
4001 .addReg(VRsrc, VRsrcUndef, AMDGPU::sub3);
4002
4003 BuildMI(LoopBB, I, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE), SRsrc)
4004 .addReg(SRsrcSub0)
4005 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub0)
4006 .addReg(SRsrcSub1)
4007 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub1)
4008 .addReg(SRsrcSub2)
4009 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub2)
4010 .addReg(SRsrcSub3)
4011 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub3);
4012
4013 // Update Rsrc operand to use the SGPR Rsrc.
4014 Rsrc.setReg(SRsrc);
4015 Rsrc.setIsKill(true);
4016
4017 // Identify all lanes with identical Rsrc operands in their VGPRs.
4018 BuildMI(LoopBB, I, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::V_CMP_EQ_U64_e64), CondReg0)
4019 .addReg(SRsrc, 0, AMDGPU::sub0_sub1)
4020 .addReg(VRsrc, 0, AMDGPU::sub0_sub1);
4021 BuildMI(LoopBB, I, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::V_CMP_EQ_U64_e64), CondReg1)
4022 .addReg(SRsrc, 0, AMDGPU::sub2_sub3)
4023 .addReg(VRsrc, 0, AMDGPU::sub2_sub3);
4024 BuildMI(LoopBB, I, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::S_AND_B64), AndCond)
4025 .addReg(CondReg0)
4026 .addReg(CondReg1);
4027
4028 MRI.setSimpleHint(SaveExec, AndCond);
4029
4030 // Update EXEC to matching lanes, saving original to SaveExec.
4031 BuildMI(LoopBB, I, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::S_AND_SAVEEXEC_B64), SaveExec)
4032 .addReg(AndCond, RegState::Kill);
4033
4034 // The original instruction is here; we insert the terminators after it.
4035 I = LoopBB.end();
4036
4037 // Update EXEC, switch all done bits to 0 and all todo bits to 1.
4038 BuildMI(LoopBB, I, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::S_XOR_B64_term), AMDGPU::EXEC)
4039 .addReg(AMDGPU::EXEC)
4040 .addReg(SaveExec);
4041 BuildMI(LoopBB, I, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::S_CBRANCH_EXECNZ)).addMBB(&LoopBB);
4042}
4043
4044// Build a waterfall loop around \p MI, replacing the VGPR \p Rsrc register
4045// with SGPRs by iterating over all unique values across all lanes.
4046static void loadSRsrcFromVGPR(const SIInstrInfo &TII, MachineInstr &MI,
4047 MachineOperand &Rsrc, MachineDominatorTree *MDT) {
4048 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent();
4049 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB.getParent();
4050 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
4051 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I(&MI);
4052 const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
4053
4054 unsigned SaveExec = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_64_XEXECRegClass);
4055
4056 // Save the EXEC mask
4057 BuildMI(MBB, I, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B64), SaveExec)
4058 .addReg(AMDGPU::EXEC);
4059
4060 // Killed uses in the instruction we are waterfalling around will be
4061 // incorrect due to the added control-flow.
4062 for (auto &MO : MI.uses()) {
4063 if (MO.isReg() && MO.isUse()) {
4064 MRI.clearKillFlags(MO.getReg());
4065 }
4066 }
4067
4068 // To insert the loop we need to split the block. Move everything after this
4069 // point to a new block, and insert a new empty block between the two.
4070 MachineBasicBlock *LoopBB = MF.CreateMachineBasicBlock();
4071 MachineBasicBlock *RemainderBB = MF.CreateMachineBasicBlock();
4072 MachineFunction::iterator MBBI(MBB);
4073 ++MBBI;
4074
4075 MF.insert(MBBI, LoopBB);
4076 MF.insert(MBBI, RemainderBB);
4077
4078 LoopBB->addSuccessor(LoopBB);
4079 LoopBB->addSuccessor(RemainderBB);
4080
4081 // Move MI to the LoopBB, and the remainder of the block to RemainderBB.
4082 MachineBasicBlock::iterator J = I++;
4083 RemainderBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(&MBB);
4084 RemainderBB->splice(RemainderBB->begin(), &MBB, I, MBB.end());
4085 LoopBB->splice(LoopBB->begin(), &MBB, J);
4086
4087 MBB.addSuccessor(LoopBB);
4088
4089 // Update dominators. We know that MBB immediately dominates LoopBB, that
4090 // LoopBB immediately dominates RemainderBB, and that RemainderBB immediately
4091 // dominates all of the successors transferred to it from MBB that MBB used
4092 // to dominate.
4093 if (MDT) {
4094 MDT->addNewBlock(LoopBB, &MBB);
4095 MDT->addNewBlock(RemainderBB, LoopBB);
4096 for (auto &Succ : RemainderBB->successors()) {
4097 if (MDT->dominates(&MBB, Succ)) {
4098 MDT->changeImmediateDominator(Succ, RemainderBB);
4099 }
4100 }
4101 }
4102
4103 emitLoadSRsrcFromVGPRLoop(TII, MRI, MBB, *LoopBB, DL, Rsrc);
4104
4105 // Restore the EXEC mask
4106 MachineBasicBlock::iterator First = RemainderBB->begin();
4107 BuildMI(*RemainderBB, First, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B64), AMDGPU::EXEC)
4108 .addReg(SaveExec);
4109}
4110
4111// Extract pointer from Rsrc and return a zero-value Rsrc replacement.
4112static std::tuple<unsigned, unsigned>
4113extractRsrcPtr(const SIInstrInfo &TII, MachineInstr &MI, MachineOperand &Rsrc) {
4114 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent();
4115 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB.getParent();
4116 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
4117
4118 // Extract the ptr from the resource descriptor.
4119 unsigned RsrcPtr =
4120 TII.buildExtractSubReg(MI, MRI, Rsrc, &AMDGPU::VReg_128RegClass,
4121 AMDGPU::sub0_sub1, &AMDGPU::VReg_64RegClass);
4122
4123 // Create an empty resource descriptor
4124 unsigned Zero64 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass);
4125 unsigned SRsrcFormatLo = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass);
4126 unsigned SRsrcFormatHi = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass);
4127 unsigned NewSRsrc = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_128RegClass);
4128 uint64_t RsrcDataFormat = TII.getDefaultRsrcDataFormat();
4129
4130 // Zero64 = 0
4131 BuildMI(MBB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII.get(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B64), Zero64)
4132 .addImm(0);
4133
4134 // SRsrcFormatLo = RSRC_DATA_FORMAT{31-0}
4135 BuildMI(MBB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII.get(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32), SRsrcFormatLo)
4136 .addImm(RsrcDataFormat & 0xFFFFFFFF);
4137
4138 // SRsrcFormatHi = RSRC_DATA_FORMAT{63-32}
4139 BuildMI(MBB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII.get(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32), SRsrcFormatHi)
4140 .addImm(RsrcDataFormat >> 32);
4141
4142 // NewSRsrc = {Zero64, SRsrcFormat}
4143 BuildMI(MBB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII.get(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE), NewSRsrc)
4144 .addReg(Zero64)
4145 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub0_sub1)
4146 .addReg(SRsrcFormatLo)
4147 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub2)
4148 .addReg(SRsrcFormatHi)
4149 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub3);
4150
4151 return std::make_tuple(RsrcPtr, NewSRsrc);
4152}
4153
4154void SIInstrInfo::legalizeOperands(MachineInstr &MI,
4155 MachineDominatorTree *MDT) const {
4156 MachineFunction &MF = *MI.getParent()->getParent();
4157 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
4158
4159 // Legalize VOP2
4160 if (isVOP2(MI) || isVOPC(MI)) {
4161 legalizeOperandsVOP2(MRI, MI);
4162 return;
4163 }
4164
4165 // Legalize VOP3
4166 if (isVOP3(MI)) {
4167 legalizeOperandsVOP3(MRI, MI);
4168 return;
4169 }
4170
4171 // Legalize SMRD
4172 if (isSMRD(MI)) {
4173 legalizeOperandsSMRD(MRI, MI);
4174 return;
4175 }
4176
4177 // Legalize REG_SEQUENCE and PHI
4178 // The register class of the operands much be the same type as the register
4179 // class of the output.
4180 if (MI.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::PHI) {
4181 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = nullptr, *SRC = nullptr, *VRC = nullptr;
4182 for (unsigned i = 1, e = MI.getNumOperands(); i != e; i += 2) {
4183 if (!MI.getOperand(i).isReg() ||
4184 !TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(MI.getOperand(i).getReg()))
4185 continue;
4186 const TargetRegisterClass *OpRC =
4187 MRI.getRegClass(MI.getOperand(i).getReg());
4188 if (RI.hasVGPRs(OpRC)) {
4189 VRC = OpRC;
4190 } else {
4191 SRC = OpRC;
4192 }
4193 }
4194
4195 // If any of the operands are VGPR registers, then they all most be
4196 // otherwise we will create illegal VGPR->SGPR copies when legalizing
4197 // them.
4198 if (VRC || !RI.isSGPRClass(getOpRegClass(MI, 0))) {
4199 if (!VRC) {
4200 assert(SRC);
4201 VRC = RI.getEquivalentVGPRClass(SRC);
4202 }
4203 RC = VRC;
4204 } else {
4205 RC = SRC;
4206 }
4207
4208 // Update all the operands so they have the same type.
4209 for (unsigned I = 1, E = MI.getNumOperands(); I != E; I += 2) {
4210 MachineOperand &Op = MI.getOperand(I);
4211 if (!Op.isReg() || !TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(Op.getReg()))
4212 continue;
4213
4214 // MI is a PHI instruction.
4215 MachineBasicBlock *InsertBB = MI.getOperand(I + 1).getMBB();
4216 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Insert = InsertBB->getFirstTerminator();
4217
4218 // Avoid creating no-op copies with the same src and dst reg class. These
4219 // confuse some of the machine passes.
4220 legalizeGenericOperand(*InsertBB, Insert, RC, Op, MRI, MI.getDebugLoc());
4221 }
4222 }
4223
4224 // REG_SEQUENCE doesn't really require operand legalization, but if one has a
4225 // VGPR dest type and SGPR sources, insert copies so all operands are
4226 // VGPRs. This seems to help operand folding / the register coalescer.
4227 if (MI.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE) {
4228 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI.getParent();
4229 const TargetRegisterClass *DstRC = getOpRegClass(MI, 0);
4230 if (RI.hasVGPRs(DstRC)) {
4231 // Update all the operands so they are VGPR register classes. These may
4232 // not be the same register class because REG_SEQUENCE supports mixing
4233 // subregister index types e.g. sub0_sub1 + sub2 + sub3
4234 for (unsigned I = 1, E = MI.getNumOperands(); I != E; I += 2) {
4235 MachineOperand &Op = MI.getOperand(I);
4236 if (!Op.isReg() || !TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(Op.getReg()))
4237 continue;
4238
4239 const TargetRegisterClass *OpRC = MRI.getRegClass(Op.getReg());
4240 const TargetRegisterClass *VRC = RI.getEquivalentVGPRClass(OpRC);
4241 if (VRC == OpRC)
4242 continue;
4243
4244 legalizeGenericOperand(*MBB, MI, VRC, Op, MRI, MI.getDebugLoc());
4245 Op.setIsKill();
4246 }
4247 }
4248
4249 return;
4250 }
4251
4252 // Legalize INSERT_SUBREG
4253 // src0 must have the same register class as dst
4254 if (MI.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::INSERT_SUBREG) {
4255 unsigned Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
4256 unsigned Src0 = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
4257 const TargetRegisterClass *DstRC = MRI.getRegClass(Dst);
4258 const TargetRegisterClass *Src0RC = MRI.getRegClass(Src0);
4259 if (DstRC != Src0RC) {
4260 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI.getParent();
4261 MachineOperand &Op = MI.getOperand(1);
4262 legalizeGenericOperand(*MBB, MI, DstRC, Op, MRI, MI.getDebugLoc());
4263 }
4264 return;
4265 }
4266
4267 // Legalize SI_INIT_M0
4268 if (MI.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::SI_INIT_M0) {
4269 MachineOperand &Src = MI.getOperand(0);
4270 if (Src.isReg() && RI.hasVGPRs(MRI.getRegClass(Src.getReg())))
4271 Src.setReg(readlaneVGPRToSGPR(Src.getReg(), MI, MRI));
4272 return;
4273 }
4274
4275 // Legalize MIMG and MUBUF/MTBUF for shaders.
4276 //
4277 // Shaders only generate MUBUF/MTBUF instructions via intrinsics or via
4278 // scratch memory access. In both cases, the legalization never involves
4279 // conversion to the addr64 form.
4280 if (isMIMG(MI) ||
4281 (AMDGPU::isShader(MF.getFunction().getCallingConv()) &&
4282 (isMUBUF(MI) || isMTBUF(MI)))) {
4283 MachineOperand *SRsrc = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::srsrc);
4284 if (SRsrc && !RI.isSGPRClass(MRI.getRegClass(SRsrc->getReg()))) {
4285 unsigned SGPR = readlaneVGPRToSGPR(SRsrc->getReg(), MI, MRI);
4286 SRsrc->setReg(SGPR);
4287 }
4288
4289 MachineOperand *SSamp = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::ssamp);
4290 if (SSamp && !RI.isSGPRClass(MRI.getRegClass(SSamp->getReg()))) {
4291 unsigned SGPR = readlaneVGPRToSGPR(SSamp->getReg(), MI, MRI);
4292 SSamp->setReg(SGPR);
4293 }
4294 return;
4295 }
4296
4297 // Legalize MUBUF* instructions.
4298 int RsrcIdx =
4299 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(MI.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::srsrc);
4300 if (RsrcIdx != -1) {
4301 // We have an MUBUF instruction
4302 MachineOperand *Rsrc = &MI.getOperand(RsrcIdx);
4303 unsigned RsrcRC = get(MI.getOpcode()).OpInfo[RsrcIdx].RegClass;
4304 if (RI.getCommonSubClass(MRI.getRegClass(Rsrc->getReg()),
4305 RI.getRegClass(RsrcRC))) {
4306 // The operands are legal.
4307 // FIXME: We may need to legalize operands besided srsrc.
4308 return;
4309 }
4310
4311 // Legalize a VGPR Rsrc.
4312 //
4313 // If the instruction is _ADDR64, we can avoid a waterfall by extracting
4314 // the base pointer from the VGPR Rsrc, adding it to the VAddr, then using
4315 // a zero-value SRsrc.
4316 //
4317 // If the instruction is _OFFSET (both idxen and offen disabled), and we
4318 // support ADDR64 instructions, we can convert to ADDR64 and do the same as
4319 // above.
4320 //
4321 // Otherwise we are on non-ADDR64 hardware, and/or we have
4322 // idxen/offen/bothen and we fall back to a waterfall loop.
4323
4324 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent();
4325
4326 MachineOperand *VAddr = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr);
4327 if (VAddr && AMDGPU::getIfAddr64Inst(MI.getOpcode()) != -1) {
4328 // This is already an ADDR64 instruction so we need to add the pointer
4329 // extracted from the resource descriptor to the current value of VAddr.
4330 unsigned NewVAddrLo = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
4331 unsigned NewVAddrHi = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
4332 unsigned NewVAddr = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VReg_64RegClass);
4333
4334 unsigned RsrcPtr, NewSRsrc;
4335 std::tie(RsrcPtr, NewSRsrc) = extractRsrcPtr(*this, MI, *Rsrc);
4336
4337 // NewVaddrLo = RsrcPtr:sub0 + VAddr:sub0
4338 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
4339 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_ADD_I32_e32), NewVAddrLo)
4340 .addReg(RsrcPtr, 0, AMDGPU::sub0)
4341 .addReg(VAddr->getReg(), 0, AMDGPU::sub0);
4342
4343 // NewVaddrHi = RsrcPtr:sub1 + VAddr:sub1
4344 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_ADDC_U32_e32), NewVAddrHi)
4345 .addReg(RsrcPtr, 0, AMDGPU::sub1)
4346 .addReg(VAddr->getReg(), 0, AMDGPU::sub1);
4347
4348 // NewVaddr = {NewVaddrHi, NewVaddrLo}
4349 BuildMI(MBB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE), NewVAddr)
4350 .addReg(NewVAddrLo)
4351 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub0)
4352 .addReg(NewVAddrHi)
4353 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub1);
4354
4355 VAddr->setReg(NewVAddr);
4356 Rsrc->setReg(NewSRsrc);
4357 } else if (!VAddr && ST.hasAddr64()) {
4358 // This instructions is the _OFFSET variant, so we need to convert it to
4359 // ADDR64.
4360 assert(MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget<GCNSubtarget>().getGeneration()
4361 < AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS &&
4362 "FIXME: Need to emit flat atomics here");
4363
4364 unsigned RsrcPtr, NewSRsrc;
4365 std::tie(RsrcPtr, NewSRsrc) = extractRsrcPtr(*this, MI, *Rsrc);
4366
4367 unsigned NewVAddr = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VReg_64RegClass);
4368 MachineOperand *VData = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata);
4369 MachineOperand *Offset = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::offset);
4370 MachineOperand *SOffset = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::soffset);
4371 unsigned Addr64Opcode = AMDGPU::getAddr64Inst(MI.getOpcode());
4372
4373 // Atomics rith return have have an additional tied operand and are
4374 // missing some of the special bits.
4375 MachineOperand *VDataIn = getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata_in);
4376 MachineInstr *Addr64;
4377
4378 if (!VDataIn) {
4379 // Regular buffer load / store.
4380 MachineInstrBuilder MIB =
4381 BuildMI(MBB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(Addr64Opcode))
4382 .add(*VData)
4383 .addReg(NewVAddr)
4384 .addReg(NewSRsrc)
4385 .add(*SOffset)
4386 .add(*Offset);
4387
4388 // Atomics do not have this operand.
4389 if (const MachineOperand *GLC =
4390 getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::glc)) {
4391 MIB.addImm(GLC->getImm());
4392 }
4393 if (const MachineOperand *DLC =
4394 getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::dlc)) {
4395 MIB.addImm(DLC->getImm());
4396 }
4397
4398 MIB.addImm(getNamedImmOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::slc));
4399
4400 if (const MachineOperand *TFE =
4401 getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::tfe)) {
4402 MIB.addImm(TFE->getImm());
4403 }
4404
4405 MIB.cloneMemRefs(MI);
4406 Addr64 = MIB;
4407 } else {
4408 // Atomics with return.
4409 Addr64 = BuildMI(MBB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(Addr64Opcode))
4410 .add(*VData)
4411 .add(*VDataIn)
4412 .addReg(NewVAddr)
4413 .addReg(NewSRsrc)
4414 .add(*SOffset)
4415 .add(*Offset)
4416 .addImm(getNamedImmOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::slc))
4417 .cloneMemRefs(MI);
4418 }
4419
4420 MI.removeFromParent();
4421
4422 // NewVaddr = {NewVaddrHi, NewVaddrLo}
4423 BuildMI(MBB, Addr64, Addr64->getDebugLoc(), get(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE),
4424 NewVAddr)
4425 .addReg(RsrcPtr, 0, AMDGPU::sub0)
4426 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub0)
4427 .addReg(RsrcPtr, 0, AMDGPU::sub1)
4428 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub1);
4429 } else {
4430 // This is another variant; legalize Rsrc with waterfall loop from VGPRs
4431 // to SGPRs.
4432 loadSRsrcFromVGPR(*this, MI, *Rsrc, MDT);
4433 }
4434 }
4435}
4436
4437void SIInstrInfo::moveToVALU(MachineInstr &TopInst,
4438 MachineDominatorTree *MDT) const {
4439 SetVectorType Worklist;
4440 Worklist.insert(&TopInst);
4441
4442 while (!Worklist.empty()) {
4443 MachineInstr &Inst = *Worklist.pop_back_val();
4444 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = Inst.getParent();
4445 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MBB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
4446
4447 unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
4448 unsigned NewOpcode = getVALUOp(Inst);
4449
4450 // Handle some special cases
4451 switch (Opcode) {
4452 default:
4453 break;
4454 case AMDGPU::S_ADD_U64_PSEUDO:
4455 case AMDGPU::S_SUB_U64_PSEUDO:
4456 splitScalar64BitAddSub(Worklist, Inst, MDT);
4457 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4458 continue;
4459 case AMDGPU::S_ADD_I32:
4460 case AMDGPU::S_SUB_I32:
4461 // FIXME: The u32 versions currently selected use the carry.
4462 if (moveScalarAddSub(Worklist, Inst, MDT))
4463 continue;
4464
4465 // Default handling
4466 break;
4467 case AMDGPU::S_AND_B64:
4468 splitScalar64BitBinaryOp(Worklist, Inst, AMDGPU::S_AND_B32, MDT);
4469 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4470 continue;
4471
4472 case AMDGPU::S_OR_B64:
4473 splitScalar64BitBinaryOp(Worklist, Inst, AMDGPU::S_OR_B32, MDT);
4474 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4475 continue;
4476
4477 case AMDGPU::S_XOR_B64:
4478 splitScalar64BitBinaryOp(Worklist, Inst, AMDGPU::S_XOR_B32, MDT);
4479 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4480 continue;
4481
4482 case AMDGPU::S_NAND_B64:
4483 splitScalar64BitBinaryOp(Worklist, Inst, AMDGPU::S_NAND_B32, MDT);
4484 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4485 continue;
4486
4487 case AMDGPU::S_NOR_B64:
4488 splitScalar64BitBinaryOp(Worklist, Inst, AMDGPU::S_NOR_B32, MDT);
4489 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4490 continue;
4491
4492 case AMDGPU::S_XNOR_B64:
4493 if (ST.hasDLInsts())
4494 splitScalar64BitBinaryOp(Worklist, Inst, AMDGPU::S_XNOR_B32, MDT);
4495 else
4496 splitScalar64BitXnor(Worklist, Inst, MDT);
4497 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4498 continue;
4499
4500 case AMDGPU::S_ANDN2_B64:
4501 splitScalar64BitBinaryOp(Worklist, Inst, AMDGPU::S_ANDN2_B32, MDT);
4502 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4503 continue;
4504
4505 case AMDGPU::S_ORN2_B64:
4506 splitScalar64BitBinaryOp(Worklist, Inst, AMDGPU::S_ORN2_B32, MDT);
4507 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4508 continue;
4509
4510 case AMDGPU::S_NOT_B64:
4511 splitScalar64BitUnaryOp(Worklist, Inst, AMDGPU::S_NOT_B32);
4512 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4513 continue;
4514
4515 case AMDGPU::S_BCNT1_I32_B64:
4516 splitScalar64BitBCNT(Worklist, Inst);
4517 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4518 continue;
4519
4520 case AMDGPU::S_BFE_I64:
4521 splitScalar64BitBFE(Worklist, Inst);
4522 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4523 continue;
4524
4525 case AMDGPU::S_LSHL_B32:
4526 if (ST.getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS) {
4527 NewOpcode = AMDGPU::V_LSHLREV_B32_e64;
4528 swapOperands(Inst);
4529 }
4530 break;
4531 case AMDGPU::S_ASHR_I32:
4532 if (ST.getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS) {
4533 NewOpcode = AMDGPU::V_ASHRREV_I32_e64;
4534 swapOperands(Inst);
4535 }
4536 break;
4537 case AMDGPU::S_LSHR_B32:
4538 if (ST.getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS) {
4539 NewOpcode = AMDGPU::V_LSHRREV_B32_e64;
4540 swapOperands(Inst);
4541 }
4542 break;
4543 case AMDGPU::S_LSHL_B64:
4544 if (ST.getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS) {
4545 NewOpcode = AMDGPU::V_LSHLREV_B64;
4546 swapOperands(Inst);
4547 }
4548 break;
4549 case AMDGPU::S_ASHR_I64:
4550 if (ST.getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS) {
4551 NewOpcode = AMDGPU::V_ASHRREV_I64;
4552 swapOperands(Inst);
4553 }
4554 break;
4555 case AMDGPU::S_LSHR_B64:
4556 if (ST.getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS) {
4557 NewOpcode = AMDGPU::V_LSHRREV_B64;
4558 swapOperands(Inst);
4559 }
4560 break;
4561
4562 case AMDGPU::S_ABS_I32:
4563 lowerScalarAbs(Worklist, Inst);
4564 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4565 continue;
4566
4567 case AMDGPU::S_CBRANCH_SCC0:
4568 case AMDGPU::S_CBRANCH_SCC1:
4569 // Clear unused bits of vcc
4570 BuildMI(*MBB, Inst, Inst.getDebugLoc(), get(AMDGPU::S_AND_B64),
4571 AMDGPU::VCC)
4572 .addReg(AMDGPU::EXEC)
4573 .addReg(AMDGPU::VCC);
4574 break;
4575
4576 case AMDGPU::S_BFE_U64:
4577 case AMDGPU::S_BFM_B64:
4578 llvm_unreachable("Moving this op to VALU not implemented");
4579
4580 case AMDGPU::S_PACK_LL_B32_B16:
4581 case AMDGPU::S_PACK_LH_B32_B16:
4582 case AMDGPU::S_PACK_HH_B32_B16:
4583 movePackToVALU(Worklist, MRI, Inst);
4584 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4585 continue;
4586
4587 case AMDGPU::S_XNOR_B32:
4588 lowerScalarXnor(Worklist, Inst);
4589 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4590 continue;
4591
4592 case AMDGPU::S_NAND_B32:
4593 splitScalarNotBinop(Worklist, Inst, AMDGPU::S_AND_B32);
4594 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4595 continue;
4596
4597 case AMDGPU::S_NOR_B32:
4598 splitScalarNotBinop(Worklist, Inst, AMDGPU::S_OR_B32);
4599 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4600 continue;
4601
4602 case AMDGPU::S_ANDN2_B32:
4603 splitScalarBinOpN2(Worklist, Inst, AMDGPU::S_AND_B32);
4604 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4605 continue;
4606
4607 case AMDGPU::S_ORN2_B32:
4608 splitScalarBinOpN2(Worklist, Inst, AMDGPU::S_OR_B32);
4609 Inst.eraseFromParent();
4610 continue;
4611 }
4612
4613 if (NewOpcode == AMDGPU::INSTRUCTION_LIST_END) {
4614 // We cannot move this instruction to the VALU, so we should try to
4615 // legalize its operands instead.
4616 legalizeOperands(Inst, MDT);
4617 continue;
4618 }
4619
4620 // Use the new VALU Opcode.
4621 const MCInstrDesc &NewDesc = get(NewOpcode);
4622 Inst.setDesc(NewDesc);
4623
4624 // Remove any references to SCC. Vector instructions can't read from it, and
4625 // We're just about to add the implicit use / defs of VCC, and we don't want
4626 // both.
4627 for (unsigned i = Inst.getNumOperands() - 1; i > 0; --i) {
4628 MachineOperand &Op = Inst.getOperand(i);
4629 if (Op.isReg() && Op.getReg() == AMDGPU::SCC) {
4630 // Only propagate through live-def of SCC.
4631 if (Op.isDef() && !Op.isDead())
4632 addSCCDefUsersToVALUWorklist(Op, Inst, Worklist);
4633 Inst.RemoveOperand(i);
4634 }
4635 }
4636
4637 if (Opcode == AMDGPU::S_SEXT_I32_I8 || Opcode == AMDGPU::S_SEXT_I32_I16) {
4638 // We are converting these to a BFE, so we need to add the missing
4639 // operands for the size and offset.
4640 unsigned Size = (Opcode == AMDGPU::S_SEXT_I32_I8) ? 8 : 16;
4641 Inst.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateImm(0));
4642 Inst.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateImm(Size));
4643
4644 } else if (Opcode == AMDGPU::S_BCNT1_I32_B32) {
4645 // The VALU version adds the second operand to the result, so insert an
4646 // extra 0 operand.
4647 Inst.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateImm(0));
4648 }
4649
4650 Inst.addImplicitDefUseOperands(*Inst.getParent()->getParent());
4651
4652 if (Opcode == AMDGPU::S_BFE_I32 || Opcode == AMDGPU::S_BFE_U32) {
4653 const MachineOperand &OffsetWidthOp = Inst.getOperand(2);
4654 // If we need to move this to VGPRs, we need to unpack the second operand
4655 // back into the 2 separate ones for bit offset and width.
4656 assert(OffsetWidthOp.isImm() &&
4657 "Scalar BFE is only implemented for constant width and offset");
4658 uint32_t Imm = OffsetWidthOp.getImm();
4659
4660 uint32_t Offset = Imm & 0x3f; // Extract bits [5:0].
4661 uint32_t BitWidth = (Imm & 0x7f0000) >> 16; // Extract bits [22:16].
4662 Inst.RemoveOperand(2); // Remove old immediate.
4663 Inst.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateImm(Offset));
4664 Inst.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateImm(BitWidth));
4665 }
4666
4667 bool HasDst = Inst.getOperand(0).isReg() && Inst.getOperand(0).isDef();
4668 unsigned NewDstReg = AMDGPU::NoRegister;
4669 if (HasDst) {
4670 unsigned DstReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
4671 if (TargetRegisterInfo::isPhysicalRegister(DstReg))
4672 continue;
4673
4674 // Update the destination register class.
4675 const TargetRegisterClass *NewDstRC = getDestEquivalentVGPRClass(Inst);
4676 if (!NewDstRC)
4677 continue;
4678
4679 if (Inst.isCopy() &&
4680 TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()) &&
4681 NewDstRC == RI.getRegClassForReg(MRI, Inst.getOperand(1).getReg())) {
4682 // Instead of creating a copy where src and dst are the same register
4683 // class, we just replace all uses of dst with src. These kinds of
4684 // copies interfere with the heuristics MachineSink uses to decide
4685 // whether or not to split a critical edge. Since the pass assumes
4686 // that copies will end up as machine instructions and not be
4687 // eliminated.
4688 addUsersToMoveToVALUWorklist(DstReg, MRI, Worklist);
4689 MRI.replaceRegWith(DstReg, Inst.getOperand(1).getReg());
4690 MRI.clearKillFlags(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg());
4691 Inst.getOperand(0).setReg(DstReg);
4692
4693 // Make sure we don't leave around a dead VGPR->SGPR copy. Normally
4694 // these are deleted later, but at -O0 it would leave a suspicious
4695 // looking illegal copy of an undef register.
4696 for (unsigned I = Inst.getNumOperands() - 1; I != 0; --I)
4697 Inst.RemoveOperand(I);
4698 Inst.setDesc(get(AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF));
4699 continue;
4700 }
4701
4702 NewDstReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(NewDstRC);
4703 MRI.replaceRegWith(DstReg, NewDstReg);
4704 }
4705
4706 // Legalize the operands
4707 legalizeOperands(Inst, MDT);
4708
4709 if (HasDst)
4710 addUsersToMoveToVALUWorklist(NewDstReg, MRI, Worklist);
4711 }
4712}
4713
4714// Add/sub require special handling to deal with carry outs.
4715bool SIInstrInfo::moveScalarAddSub(SetVectorType &Worklist, MachineInstr &Inst,
4716 MachineDominatorTree *MDT) const {
4717 if (ST.hasAddNoCarry()) {
4718 // Assume there is no user of scc since we don't select this in that case.
4719 // Since scc isn't used, it doesn't really matter if the i32 or u32 variant
4720 // is used.
4721
4722 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *Inst.getParent();
4723 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MBB.getParent()->getRegInfo();
4724
4725 unsigned OldDstReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
4726 unsigned ResultReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
4727
4728 unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
4729 assert(Opc == AMDGPU::S_ADD_I32 || Opc == AMDGPU::S_SUB_I32);
4730
4731 unsigned NewOpc = Opc == AMDGPU::S_ADD_I32 ?
4732 AMDGPU::V_ADD_U32_e64 : AMDGPU::V_SUB_U32_e64;
4733
4734 assert(Inst.getOperand(3).getReg() == AMDGPU::SCC);
4735 Inst.RemoveOperand(3);
4736
4737 Inst.setDesc(get(NewOpc));
4738 Inst.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateImm(0)); // clamp bit
4739 Inst.addImplicitDefUseOperands(*MBB.getParent());
4740 MRI.replaceRegWith(OldDstReg, ResultReg);
4741 legalizeOperands(Inst, MDT);
4742
4743 addUsersToMoveToVALUWorklist(ResultReg, MRI, Worklist);
4744 return true;
4745 }
4746
4747 return false;
4748}
