4750void SIInstrInfo::lowerScalarAbs(SetVectorType &Worklist,
4751 MachineInstr &Inst) const {
4752 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *Inst.getParent();
4753 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MBB.getParent()->getRegInfo();
4754 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MII = Inst;
4755 DebugLoc DL = Inst.getDebugLoc();
4756
4757 MachineOperand &Dest = Inst.getOperand(0);
4758 MachineOperand &Src = Inst.getOperand(1);
4759 unsigned TmpReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
4760 unsigned ResultReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
4761
4762 unsigned SubOp = ST.hasAddNoCarry() ?
4763 AMDGPU::V_SUB_U32_e32 : AMDGPU::V_SUB_I32_e32;
4764
4765 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(SubOp), TmpReg)
4766 .addImm(0)
4767 .addReg(Src.getReg());
4768
4769 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_MAX_I32_e64), ResultReg)
4770 .addReg(Src.getReg())
4771 .addReg(TmpReg);
4772
4773 MRI.replaceRegWith(Dest.getReg(), ResultReg);
4774 addUsersToMoveToVALUWorklist(ResultReg, MRI, Worklist);
4775}
4776
4777void SIInstrInfo::lowerScalarXnor(SetVectorType &Worklist,
4778 MachineInstr &Inst) const {
4779 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *Inst.getParent();
4780 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MBB.getParent()->getRegInfo();
4781 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MII = Inst;
4782 const DebugLoc &DL = Inst.getDebugLoc();
4783
4784 MachineOperand &Dest = Inst.getOperand(0);
4785 MachineOperand &Src0 = Inst.getOperand(1);
4786 MachineOperand &Src1 = Inst.getOperand(2);
4787
4788 if (ST.hasDLInsts()) {
4789 unsigned NewDest = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
4790 legalizeGenericOperand(MBB, MII, &AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass, Src0, MRI, DL);
4791 legalizeGenericOperand(MBB, MII, &AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass, Src1, MRI, DL);
4792
4793 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_XNOR_B32_e64), NewDest)
4794 .add(Src0)
4795 .add(Src1);
4796
4797 MRI.replaceRegWith(Dest.getReg(), NewDest);
4798 addUsersToMoveToVALUWorklist(NewDest, MRI, Worklist);
4799 } else {
4800 // Using the identity !(x ^ y) == (!x ^ y) == (x ^ !y), we can
4801 // invert either source and then perform the XOR. If either source is a
4802 // scalar register, then we can leave the inversion on the scalar unit to
4803 // acheive a better distrubution of scalar and vector instructions.
4804 bool Src0IsSGPR = Src0.isReg() &&
4805 RI.isSGPRClass(MRI.getRegClass(Src0.getReg()));
4806 bool Src1IsSGPR = Src1.isReg() &&
4807 RI.isSGPRClass(MRI.getRegClass(Src1.getReg()));
4808 MachineInstr *Not = nullptr;
4809 MachineInstr *Xor = nullptr;
4810 unsigned Temp = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_32_XM0RegClass);
4811 unsigned NewDest = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_32_XM0RegClass);
4812
4813 // Build a pair of scalar instructions and add them to the work list.
4814 // The next iteration over the work list will lower these to the vector
4815 // unit as necessary.
4816 if (Src0IsSGPR) {
4817 Not = BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(AMDGPU::S_NOT_B32), Temp)
4818 .add(Src0);
4819 Xor = BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(AMDGPU::S_XOR_B32), NewDest)
4820 .addReg(Temp)
4821 .add(Src1);
4822 } else if (Src1IsSGPR) {
4823 Not = BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(AMDGPU::S_NOT_B32), Temp)
4824 .add(Src1);
4825 Xor = BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(AMDGPU::S_XOR_B32), NewDest)
4826 .add(Src0)
4827 .addReg(Temp);
4828 } else {
4829 Xor = BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(AMDGPU::S_XOR_B32), Temp)
4830 .add(Src0)
4831 .add(Src1);
4832 Not = BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(AMDGPU::S_NOT_B32), NewDest)
4833 .addReg(Temp);
4834 Worklist.insert(Not);
4835 }
4836
4837 MRI.replaceRegWith(Dest.getReg(), NewDest);
4838
4839 Worklist.insert(Xor);
4840
4841 addUsersToMoveToVALUWorklist(NewDest, MRI, Worklist);
4842 }
4843}

4903void SIInstrInfo::splitScalar64BitUnaryOp(
4904 SetVectorType &Worklist, MachineInstr &Inst,
4905 unsigned Opcode) const {
4906 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *Inst.getParent();
4907 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MBB.getParent()->getRegInfo();
4908
4909 MachineOperand &Dest = Inst.getOperand(0);
4910 MachineOperand &Src0 = Inst.getOperand(1);
4911 DebugLoc DL = Inst.getDebugLoc();
4912
4913 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MII = Inst;
4914
4915 const MCInstrDesc &InstDesc = get(Opcode);
4916 const TargetRegisterClass *Src0RC = Src0.isReg() ?
4917 MRI.getRegClass(Src0.getReg()) :
4918 &AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass;
4919
4920 const TargetRegisterClass *Src0SubRC = RI.getSubRegClass(Src0RC, AMDGPU::sub0);
4921
4922 MachineOperand SrcReg0Sub0 = buildExtractSubRegOrImm(MII, MRI, Src0, Src0RC,
4923 AMDGPU::sub0, Src0SubRC);
4924
4925 const TargetRegisterClass *DestRC = MRI.getRegClass(Dest.getReg());
4926 const TargetRegisterClass *NewDestRC = RI.getEquivalentVGPRClass(DestRC);
4927 const TargetRegisterClass *NewDestSubRC = RI.getSubRegClass(NewDestRC, AMDGPU::sub0);
4928
4929 unsigned DestSub0 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(NewDestSubRC);
4930 MachineInstr &LoHalf = *BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, InstDesc, DestSub0).add(SrcReg0Sub0);
4931
4932 MachineOperand SrcReg0Sub1 = buildExtractSubRegOrImm(MII, MRI, Src0, Src0RC,
4933 AMDGPU::sub1, Src0SubRC);
4934
4935 unsigned DestSub1 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(NewDestSubRC);
4936 MachineInstr &HiHalf = *BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, InstDesc, DestSub1).add(SrcReg0Sub1);
4937
4938 unsigned FullDestReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(NewDestRC);
4939 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE), FullDestReg)
4940 .addReg(DestSub0)
4941 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub0)
4942 .addReg(DestSub1)
4943 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub1);
4944
4945 MRI.replaceRegWith(Dest.getReg(), FullDestReg);
4946
4947 Worklist.insert(&LoHalf);
4948 Worklist.insert(&HiHalf);
4949
4950 // We don't need to legalizeOperands here because for a single operand, src0
4951 // will support any kind of input.
4952
4953 // Move all users of this moved value.
4954 addUsersToMoveToVALUWorklist(FullDestReg, MRI, Worklist);
4955}

4957void SIInstrInfo::splitScalar64BitAddSub(SetVectorType &Worklist,
4958 MachineInstr &Inst,
4959 MachineDominatorTree *MDT) const {
4960 bool IsAdd = (Inst.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_ADD_U64_PSEUDO);
4961
4962 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *Inst.getParent();
4963 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MBB.getParent()->getRegInfo();
4964
4965 unsigned FullDestReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VReg_64RegClass);
4966 unsigned DestSub0 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
4967 unsigned DestSub1 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
4968
4969 unsigned CarryReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_64_XEXECRegClass);
4970 unsigned DeadCarryReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_64_XEXECRegClass);
4971
4972 MachineOperand &Dest = Inst.getOperand(0);
4973 MachineOperand &Src0 = Inst.getOperand(1);
4974 MachineOperand &Src1 = Inst.getOperand(2);
4975 const DebugLoc &DL = Inst.getDebugLoc();
4976 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MII = Inst;
4977
4978 const TargetRegisterClass *Src0RC = MRI.getRegClass(Src0.getReg());
4979 const TargetRegisterClass *Src1RC = MRI.getRegClass(Src1.getReg());
4980 const TargetRegisterClass *Src0SubRC = RI.getSubRegClass(Src0RC, AMDGPU::sub0);
4981 const TargetRegisterClass *Src1SubRC = RI.getSubRegClass(Src1RC, AMDGPU::sub0);
4982
4983 MachineOperand SrcReg0Sub0 = buildExtractSubRegOrImm(MII, MRI, Src0, Src0RC,
4984 AMDGPU::sub0, Src0SubRC);
4985 MachineOperand SrcReg1Sub0 = buildExtractSubRegOrImm(MII, MRI, Src1, Src1RC,
4986 AMDGPU::sub0, Src1SubRC);
4987
4988
4989 MachineOperand SrcReg0Sub1 = buildExtractSubRegOrImm(MII, MRI, Src0, Src0RC,
4990 AMDGPU::sub1, Src0SubRC);
4991 MachineOperand SrcReg1Sub1 = buildExtractSubRegOrImm(MII, MRI, Src1, Src1RC,
4992 AMDGPU::sub1, Src1SubRC);
4993
4994 unsigned LoOpc = IsAdd ? AMDGPU::V_ADD_I32_e64 : AMDGPU::V_SUB_I32_e64;
4995 MachineInstr *LoHalf =
4996 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(LoOpc), DestSub0)
4997 .addReg(CarryReg, RegState::Define)
4998 .add(SrcReg0Sub0)
4999 .add(SrcReg1Sub0)
5000 .addImm(0); // clamp bit
5001
5002 unsigned HiOpc = IsAdd ? AMDGPU::V_ADDC_U32_e64 : AMDGPU::V_SUBB_U32_e64;
5003 MachineInstr *HiHalf =
5004 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(HiOpc), DestSub1)
5005 .addReg(DeadCarryReg, RegState::Define | RegState::Dead)
5006 .add(SrcReg0Sub1)
5007 .add(SrcReg1Sub1)
5008 .addReg(CarryReg, RegState::Kill)
5009 .addImm(0); // clamp bit
5010
5011 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE), FullDestReg)
5012 .addReg(DestSub0)
5013 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub0)
5014 .addReg(DestSub1)
5015 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub1);
5016
5017 MRI.replaceRegWith(Dest.getReg(), FullDestReg);
5018
5019 // Try to legalize the operands in case we need to swap the order to keep it
5020 // valid.
5021 legalizeOperands(*LoHalf, MDT);
5022 legalizeOperands(*HiHalf, MDT);
5023
5024 // Move all users of this moved vlaue.
5025 addUsersToMoveToVALUWorklist(FullDestReg, MRI, Worklist);
5026}

5134void SIInstrInfo::splitScalar64BitBCNT(

5140 const DebugLoc &DL = Inst.getDebugLoc();
5141
5142 MachineOperand &Dest = Inst.getOperand(0);
5143 MachineOperand &Src = Inst.getOperand(1);
5144
5145 const MCInstrDesc &InstDesc = get(AMDGPU::V_BCNT_U32_B32_e64);
5146 const TargetRegisterClass *SrcRC = Src.isReg() ?
5147 MRI.getRegClass(Src.getReg()) :
5148 &AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass;
5149
5150 unsigned MidReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
5151 unsigned ResultReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
5152
5153 const TargetRegisterClass *SrcSubRC = RI.getSubRegClass(SrcRC, AMDGPU::sub0);
5154
5155 MachineOperand SrcRegSub0 = buildExtractSubRegOrImm(MII, MRI, Src, SrcRC,
5156 AMDGPU::sub0, SrcSubRC);
5157 MachineOperand SrcRegSub1 = buildExtractSubRegOrImm(MII, MRI, Src, SrcRC,
5158 AMDGPU::sub1, SrcSubRC);
5159
5160 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, InstDesc, MidReg).add(SrcRegSub0).addImm(0);
5161
5162 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, InstDesc, ResultReg).add(SrcRegSub1).addReg(MidReg);
5163
5164 MRI.replaceRegWith(Dest.getReg(), ResultReg);
5165
5166 // We don't need to legalize operands here. src0 for etiher instruction can be
5167 // an SGPR, and the second input is unused or determined here.
5168 addUsersToMoveToVALUWorklist(ResultReg, MRI, Worklist);
5169}
5170
5171void SIInstrInfo::splitScalar64BitBFE(SetVectorType &Worklist,
5172 MachineInstr &Inst) const {
5173 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *Inst.getParent();
5174 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MBB.getParent()->getRegInfo();
5175 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MII = Inst;
5176 const DebugLoc &DL = Inst.getDebugLoc();
5177
5178 MachineOperand &Dest = Inst.getOperand(0);
5179 uint32_t Imm = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
5180 uint32_t Offset = Imm & 0x3f; // Extract bits [5:0].
5181 uint32_t BitWidth = (Imm & 0x7f0000) >> 16; // Extract bits [22:16].
5182
5183 (void) Offset;
5184
5185 // Only sext_inreg cases handled.
5186 assert(Inst.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_BFE_I64 && BitWidth <= 32 &&
5187 Offset == 0 && "Not implemented");
5188
5189 if (BitWidth < 32) {
5190 unsigned MidRegLo = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
5191 unsigned MidRegHi = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
5192 unsigned ResultReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VReg_64RegClass);
5193
5194 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_BFE_I32), MidRegLo)
5195 .addReg(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg(), 0, AMDGPU::sub0)
5196 .addImm(0)
5197 .addImm(BitWidth);
5198
5199 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_ASHRREV_I32_e32), MidRegHi)
5200 .addImm(31)
5201 .addReg(MidRegLo);
5202
5203 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE), ResultReg)
5204 .addReg(MidRegLo)
5205 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub0)
5206 .addReg(MidRegHi)
5207 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub1);
5208
5209 MRI.replaceRegWith(Dest.getReg(), ResultReg);
5210 addUsersToMoveToVALUWorklist(ResultReg, MRI, Worklist);
5211 return;
5212 }
5213
5214 MachineOperand &Src = Inst.getOperand(1);
5215 unsigned TmpReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
5216 unsigned ResultReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VReg_64RegClass);
5217
5218 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_ASHRREV_I32_e64), TmpReg)
5219 .addImm(31)
5220 .addReg(Src.getReg(), 0, AMDGPU::sub0);
5221
5222 BuildMI(MBB, MII, DL, get(TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE), ResultReg)
5223 .addReg(Src.getReg(), 0, AMDGPU::sub0)
5224 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub0)
5225 .addReg(TmpReg)
5226 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub1);
5227
5228 MRI.replaceRegWith(Dest.getReg(), ResultReg);
5229 addUsersToMoveToVALUWorklist(ResultReg, MRI, Worklist);
5230}
5231
5232void SIInstrInfo::addUsersToMoveToVALUWorklist(
5233 unsigned DstReg,
5234 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
5235 SetVectorType &Worklist) const {
5236 for (MachineRegisterInfo::use_iterator I = MRI.use_begin(DstReg),
5237 E = MRI.use_end(); I != E;) {
5238 MachineInstr &UseMI = *I->getParent();
5239
5240 unsigned OpNo = 0;
5241
5242 switch (UseMI.getOpcode()) {
5243 case AMDGPU::COPY:
5244 case AMDGPU::WQM:
5245 case AMDGPU::WWM:
5246 case AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE:
5247 case AMDGPU::PHI:
5248 case AMDGPU::INSERT_SUBREG:
5249 break;
5250 default:
5251 OpNo = I.getOperandNo();
5252 break;
5253 }
5254
5255 if (!RI.hasVGPRs(getOpRegClass(UseMI, OpNo))) {
5256 Worklist.insert(&UseMI);
5257
5258 do {
5259 ++I;
5260 } while (I != E && I->getParent() == &UseMI);
5261 } else {
5262 ++I;
5263 }
5264 }
5265}
5266
5267void SIInstrInfo::movePackToVALU(SetVectorType &Worklist,
5268 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
5269 MachineInstr &Inst) const {
5270 unsigned ResultReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
5271 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = Inst.getParent();
5272 MachineOperand &Src0 = Inst.getOperand(1);
5273 MachineOperand &Src1 = Inst.getOperand(2);
5274 const DebugLoc &DL = Inst.getDebugLoc();
5275
5276 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
5277 case AMDGPU::S_PACK_LL_B32_B16: {
5278 unsigned ImmReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
5279 unsigned TmpReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
5280
5281 // FIXME: Can do a lot better if we know the high bits of src0 or src1 are
5282 // 0.
5283 BuildMI(*MBB, Inst, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32), ImmReg)
5284 .addImm(0xffff);
5285
5286 BuildMI(*MBB, Inst, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_AND_B32_e64), TmpReg)
5287 .addReg(ImmReg, RegState::Kill)
5288 .add(Src0);
5289
5290 BuildMI(*MBB, Inst, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_LSHL_OR_B32), ResultReg)
5291 .add(Src1)
5292 .addImm(16)
5293 .addReg(TmpReg, RegState::Kill);
5294 break;
5295 }
5296 case AMDGPU::S_PACK_LH_B32_B16: {
5297 unsigned ImmReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
5298 BuildMI(*MBB, Inst, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32), ImmReg)
5299 .addImm(0xffff);
5300 BuildMI(*MBB, Inst, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_BFI_B32), ResultReg)
5301 .addReg(ImmReg, RegState::Kill)
5302 .add(Src0)
5303 .add(Src1);
5304 break;
5305 }
5306 case AMDGPU::S_PACK_HH_B32_B16: {
5307 unsigned ImmReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
5308 unsigned TmpReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
5309 BuildMI(*MBB, Inst, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_LSHRREV_B32_e64), TmpReg)
5310 .addImm(16)
5311 .add(Src0);
5312 BuildMI(*MBB, Inst, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32), ImmReg)
5313 .addImm(0xffff0000);
5314 BuildMI(*MBB, Inst, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_AND_OR_B32), ResultReg)
5315 .add(Src1)
5316 .addReg(ImmReg, RegState::Kill)
5317 .addReg(TmpReg, RegState::Kill);
5318 break;
5319 }
5320 default:
5321 llvm_unreachable("unhandled s_pack_* instruction");
5322 }
5323
5324 MachineOperand &Dest = Inst.getOperand(0);
5325 MRI.replaceRegWith(Dest.getReg(), ResultReg);
5326 addUsersToMoveToVALUWorklist(ResultReg, MRI, Worklist);
5327}
5328
5329void SIInstrInfo::addSCCDefUsersToVALUWorklist(MachineOperand &Op,
5330 MachineInstr &SCCDefInst,
5331 SetVectorType &Worklist) const {
5332 // Ensure that def inst defines SCC, which is still live.
5333 assert(Op.isReg() && Op.getReg() == AMDGPU::SCC && Op.isDef() &&
5334 !Op.isDead() && Op.getParent() == &SCCDefInst);
5335 // This assumes that all the users of SCC are in the same block
5336 // as the SCC def.
5337 for (MachineInstr &MI : // Skip the def inst itself.
5338 make_range(std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(SCCDefInst)),
5339 SCCDefInst.getParent()->end())) {
5340 // Check if SCC is used first.
5341 if (MI.findRegisterUseOperandIdx(AMDGPU::SCC, false, &RI) != -1)
5342 Worklist.insert(&MI);
5343 // Exit if we find another SCC def.
5344 if (MI.findRegisterDefOperandIdx(AMDGPU::SCC, false, false, &RI) != -1)
5345 return;
5346 }
5347}
5348
5349const TargetRegisterClass *SIInstrInfo::getDestEquivalentVGPRClass(
5350 const MachineInstr &Inst) const {
5351 const TargetRegisterClass *NewDstRC = getOpRegClass(Inst, 0);
5352
5353 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
5354 // For target instructions, getOpRegClass just returns the virtual register
5355 // class associated with the operand, so we need to find an equivalent VGPR
5356 // register class in order to move the instruction to the VALU.
5357 case AMDGPU::COPY:
5358 case AMDGPU::PHI:
5359 case AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE:
5360 case AMDGPU::INSERT_SUBREG:
5361 case AMDGPU::WQM:
5362 case AMDGPU::WWM:
5363 if (RI.hasVGPRs(NewDstRC))
5364 return nullptr;
5365
5366 NewDstRC = RI.getEquivalentVGPRClass(NewDstRC);
5367 if (!NewDstRC)
5368 return nullptr;
5369 return NewDstRC;
5370 default:
5371 return NewDstRC;
5372 }
5373}
5374
5375// Find the one SGPR operand we are allowed to use.
5376unsigned SIInstrInfo::findUsedSGPR(const MachineInstr &MI,
5377 int OpIndices[3]) const {
5378 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MI.getDesc();
5379
5380 // Find the one SGPR operand we are allowed to use.
5381 //
5382 // First we need to consider the instruction's operand requirements before
5383 // legalizing. Some operands are required to be SGPRs, such as implicit uses
5384 // of VCC, but we are still bound by the constant bus requirement to only use
5385 // one.
5386 //
5387 // If the operand's class is an SGPR, we can never move it.
5388
5389 unsigned SGPRReg = findImplicitSGPRRead(MI);
5390 if (SGPRReg != AMDGPU::NoRegister)
5391 return SGPRReg;
5392
5393 unsigned UsedSGPRs[3] = { AMDGPU::NoRegister };
5394 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MI.getParent()->getParent()->getRegInfo();
5395
5396 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 3; ++i) {
5397 int Idx = OpIndices[i];
5398 if (Idx == -1)
5399 break;
5400
5401 const MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(Idx);
5402 if (!MO.isReg())
5403 continue;
5404
5405 // Is this operand statically required to be an SGPR based on the operand
5406 // constraints?
5407 const TargetRegisterClass *OpRC = RI.getRegClass(Desc.OpInfo[Idx].RegClass);
5408 bool IsRequiredSGPR = RI.isSGPRClass(OpRC);
5409 if (IsRequiredSGPR)
5410 return MO.getReg();
5411
5412 // If this could be a VGPR or an SGPR, Check the dynamic register class.
5413 unsigned Reg = MO.getReg();
5414 const TargetRegisterClass *RegRC = MRI.getRegClass(Reg);
5415 if (RI.isSGPRClass(RegRC))
5416 UsedSGPRs[i] = Reg;
5417 }
5418
5419 // We don't have a required SGPR operand, so we have a bit more freedom in
5420 // selecting operands to move.
5421
5422 // Try to select the most used SGPR. If an SGPR is equal to one of the
5423 // others, we choose that.
5424 //
5425 // e.g.
5426 // V_FMA_F32 v0, s0, s0, s0 -> No moves
5427 // V_FMA_F32 v0, s0, s1, s0 -> Move s1
5428
5429 // TODO: If some of the operands are 64-bit SGPRs and some 32, we should
5430 // prefer those.
5431
5432 if (UsedSGPRs[0] != AMDGPU::NoRegister) {
5433 if (UsedSGPRs[0] == UsedSGPRs[1] || UsedSGPRs[0] == UsedSGPRs[2])
5434 SGPRReg = UsedSGPRs[0];
5435 }
5436
5437 if (SGPRReg == AMDGPU::NoRegister && UsedSGPRs[1] != AMDGPU::NoRegister) {
5438 if (UsedSGPRs[1] == UsedSGPRs[2])
5439 SGPRReg = UsedSGPRs[1];
5440 }
5441
5442 return SGPRReg;
5443}

5446 unsigned OperandName) const {
5447 int Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(MI.getOpcode(), OperandName);
5448 if (Idx == -1)
5449 return nullptr;
5450
5451 return &MI.getOperand(Idx);

5453
5454uint64_t SIInstrInfo::getDefaultRsrcDataFormat() const {
5455 if (ST.getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX10) {
5456 return (16ULL << 44) | // IMG_FORMAT_32_FLOAT
5457 (1ULL << 56) | // RESOURCE_LEVEL = 1
5458 (3ULL << 60); // OOB_SELECT = 3
5459 }
5460
5461 uint64_t RsrcDataFormat = AMDGPU::RSRC_DATA_FORMAT;
5462 if (ST.isAmdHsaOS()) {
5463 // Set ATC = 1. GFX9 doesn't have this bit.
5464 if (ST.getGeneration() <= AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS)
5465 RsrcDataFormat |= (1ULL << 56);
5466
5467 // Set MTYPE = 2 (MTYPE_UC = uncached). GFX9 doesn't have this.
5468 // BTW, it disables TC L2 and therefore decreases performance.
5469 if (ST.getGeneration() == AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS)
5470 RsrcDataFormat |= (2ULL << 59);
5471 }
5472
5473 return RsrcDataFormat;
5474}
5475
5476uint64_t SIInstrInfo::getScratchRsrcWords23() const {
5477 uint64_t Rsrc23 = getDefaultRsrcDataFormat() |
5478 AMDGPU::RSRC_TID_ENABLE |
5479 0xffffffff; // Size;
5480
5481 // GFX9 doesn't have ELEMENT_SIZE.
5482 if (ST.getGeneration() <= AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS) {
5483 uint64_t EltSizeValue = Log2_32(ST.getMaxPrivateElementSize()) - 1;
5484 Rsrc23 |= EltSizeValue << AMDGPU::RSRC_ELEMENT_SIZE_SHIFT;
5485 }
5486
5487 // IndexStride = 64 / 32.
5488 uint64_t IndexStride = ST.getGeneration() <= AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX9 ? 3 : 2;
5489 Rsrc23 |= IndexStride << AMDGPU::RSRC_INDEX_STRIDE_SHIFT;
5490
5491 // If TID_ENABLE is set, DATA_FORMAT specifies stride bits [14:17].
5492 // Clear them unless we want a huge stride.
5493 if (ST.getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS &&
5494 ST.getGeneration() <= AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX9)
5495 Rsrc23 &= ~AMDGPU::RSRC_DATA_FORMAT;
5496
5497 return Rsrc23;
5498}

5561unsigned SIInstrInfo::getInstBundleSize(const MachineInstr &MI) const {
5562 unsigned Size = 0;
5563 MachineBasicBlock::const_instr_iterator I = MI.getIterator();
5564 MachineBasicBlock::const_instr_iterator E = MI.getParent()->instr_end();
5565 while (++I != E && I->isInsideBundle()) {
5566 assert(!I->isBundle() && "No nested bundle!");
5567 Size += getInstSizeInBytes(*I);
5568 }
5569
5570 return Size;
5571}
5572
5573unsigned SIInstrInfo::getInstSizeInBytes(const MachineInstr &MI) const {
5574 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode();
5575 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = getMCOpcodeFromPseudo(Opc);
5576 unsigned DescSize = Desc.getSize();
5577
5578 // If we have a definitive size, we can use it. Otherwise we need to inspect
5579 // the operands to know the size.
5580 if (isFixedSize(MI))
5581 return DescSize;
5582
5583 // 4-byte instructions may have a 32-bit literal encoded after them. Check
5584 // operands that coud ever be literals.
5585 if (isVALU(MI) || isSALU(MI)) {
5586 int Src0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src0);
5587 if (Src0Idx == -1)
5588 return DescSize; // No operands.
5589
5590 if (isLiteralConstantLike(MI.getOperand(Src0Idx), Desc.OpInfo[Src0Idx]))
5591 return isVOP3(MI) ? 12 : (DescSize + 4);
5592
5593 int Src1Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src1);
5594 if (Src1Idx == -1)
5595 return DescSize;
5596
5597 if (isLiteralConstantLike(MI.getOperand(Src1Idx), Desc.OpInfo[Src1Idx]))
5598 return isVOP3(MI) ? 12 : (DescSize + 4);
5599
5600 int Src2Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src2);
5601 if (Src2Idx == -1)
5602 return DescSize;
5603
5604 if (isLiteralConstantLike(MI.getOperand(Src2Idx), Desc.OpInfo[Src2Idx]))
5605 return isVOP3(MI) ? 12 : (DescSize + 4);
5606
5607 return DescSize;
5608 }
5609
5610 // Check whether we have extra NSA words.
5611 if (isMIMG(MI)) {
5612 int VAddr0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr0);
5613 if (VAddr0Idx < 0)
5614 return 8;
5615
5616 int RSrcIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::srsrc);
5617 return 8 + 4 * ((RSrcIdx - VAddr0Idx + 2) / 4);
5618 }
5619
5620 switch (Opc) {
5621 case TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF:
5622 case TargetOpcode::KILL:
5623 case TargetOpcode::DBG_VALUE:
5624 case TargetOpcode::EH_LABEL:
5625 return 0;
5626 case TargetOpcode::BUNDLE:
5627 return getInstBundleSize(MI);
5628 case TargetOpcode::INLINEASM:
5629 case TargetOpcode::INLINEASM_BR: {
5630 const MachineFunction *MF = MI.getParent()->getParent();
5631 const char *AsmStr = MI.getOperand(0).getSymbolName();
5632 return getInlineAsmLength(AsmStr, *MF->getTarget().getMCAsmInfo(),
5633 &MF->getSubtarget());
5634 }
5635 default:
5636 return DescSize;
5637 }
5638}

5640bool SIInstrInfo::mayAccessFlatAddressSpace(const MachineInstr &MI) const {
5641 if (!isFLAT(MI))
5642 return false;
5643
5644 if (MI.memoperands_empty())
5645 return true;
5646
5647 for (const MachineMemOperand *MMO : MI.memoperands()) {
5648 if (MMO->getAddrSpace() == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS)
5649 return true;
5650 }
5651 return false;

5657
5658void SIInstrInfo::convertNonUniformIfRegion(MachineBasicBlock *IfEntry,
5659 MachineBasicBlock *IfEnd) const {
5660 MachineBasicBlock::iterator TI = IfEntry->getFirstTerminator();
5661 assert(TI != IfEntry->end());
5662
5663 MachineInstr *Branch = &(*TI);
5664 MachineFunction *MF = IfEntry->getParent();
5665 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = IfEntry->getParent()->getRegInfo();
5666
5667 if (Branch->getOpcode() == AMDGPU::SI_NON_UNIFORM_BRCOND_PSEUDO) {
5668 unsigned DstReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass);
5669 MachineInstr *SIIF =
5670 BuildMI(*MF, Branch->getDebugLoc(), get(AMDGPU::SI_IF), DstReg)
5671 .add(Branch->getOperand(0))
5672 .add(Branch->getOperand(1));
5673 MachineInstr *SIEND =
5674 BuildMI(*MF, Branch->getDebugLoc(), get(AMDGPU::SI_END_CF))
5675 .addReg(DstReg);
5676
5677 IfEntry->erase(TI);
5678 IfEntry->insert(IfEntry->end(), SIIF);
5679 IfEnd->insert(IfEnd->getFirstNonPHI(), SIEND);
5680 }
5681}
5682
5683void SIInstrInfo::convertNonUniformLoopRegion(
5684 MachineBasicBlock *LoopEntry, MachineBasicBlock *LoopEnd) const {
5685 MachineBasicBlock::iterator TI = LoopEnd->getFirstTerminator();
5686 // We expect 2 terminators, one conditional and one unconditional.
5687 assert(TI != LoopEnd->end());
5688
5689 MachineInstr *Branch = &(*TI);
5690 MachineFunction *MF = LoopEnd->getParent();
5691 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = LoopEnd->getParent()->getRegInfo();
5692
5693 if (Branch->getOpcode() == AMDGPU::SI_NON_UNIFORM_BRCOND_PSEUDO) {
5694
5695 unsigned DstReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass);
5696 unsigned BackEdgeReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass);
5697 MachineInstrBuilder HeaderPHIBuilder =
5698 BuildMI(*(MF), Branch->getDebugLoc(), get(TargetOpcode::PHI), DstReg);
5699 for (MachineBasicBlock::pred_iterator PI = LoopEntry->pred_begin(),
5700 E = LoopEntry->pred_end();
5701 PI != E; ++PI) {
5702 if (*PI == LoopEnd) {
5703 HeaderPHIBuilder.addReg(BackEdgeReg);
5704 } else {
5705 MachineBasicBlock *PMBB = *PI;
5706 unsigned ZeroReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass);
5707 materializeImmediate(*PMBB, PMBB->getFirstTerminator(), DebugLoc(),
5708 ZeroReg, 0);
5709 HeaderPHIBuilder.addReg(ZeroReg);
5710 }
5711 HeaderPHIBuilder.addMBB(*PI);
5712 }
5713 MachineInstr *HeaderPhi = HeaderPHIBuilder;
5714 MachineInstr *SIIFBREAK = BuildMI(*(MF), Branch->getDebugLoc(),
5715 get(AMDGPU::SI_IF_BREAK), BackEdgeReg)
5716 .addReg(DstReg)
5717 .add(Branch->getOperand(0));
5718 MachineInstr *SILOOP =
5719 BuildMI(*(MF), Branch->getDebugLoc(), get(AMDGPU::SI_LOOP))
5720 .addReg(BackEdgeReg)
5721 .addMBB(LoopEntry);
5722
5723 LoopEntry->insert(LoopEntry->begin(), HeaderPhi);
5724 LoopEnd->erase(TI);
5725 LoopEnd->insert(LoopEnd->end(), SIIFBREAK);
5726 LoopEnd->insert(LoopEnd->end(), SILOOP);
5727 }
5728}

5779MachineInstrBuilder
5780SIInstrInfo::getAddNoCarry(MachineBasicBlock &MBB,
5781 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I,
5782 const DebugLoc &DL,
5783 unsigned DestReg) const {
5784 if (ST.hasAddNoCarry())
5785 return BuildMI(MBB, I, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_ADD_U32_e64), DestReg);
5786

5788 unsigned UnusedCarry = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass);
5789 MRI.setRegAllocationHint(UnusedCarry, 0, AMDGPU::VCC);
5790
5791 return BuildMI(MBB, I, DL, get(AMDGPU::V_ADD_I32_e64), DestReg)
5792 .addReg(UnusedCarry, RegState::Define | RegState::Dead);

5816bool SIInstrInfo::isBufferSMRD(const MachineInstr &MI) const {
5817 if (!isSMRD(MI))
5818 return false;
5819
5820 // Check that it is using a buffer resource.
5821 int Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(MI.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::sbase);
5822 if (Idx == -1) // e.g. s_memtime
5823 return false;
5824
5825 const auto RCID = MI.getDesc().OpInfo[Idx].RegClass;
5826 return RCID == AMDGPU::SReg_128RegClassID;
5827}

5829// This must be kept in sync with the SIEncodingFamily class in SIInstrInfo.td
5830enum SIEncodingFamily {
5831 SI = 0,
5832 VI = 1,
5833 SDWA = 2,
5834 SDWA9 = 3,
5835 GFX80 = 4,
5836 GFX9 = 5,
5837 GFX10 = 6,
5838 SDWA10 = 7
5839};
5840
5841static SIEncodingFamily subtargetEncodingFamily(const GCNSubtarget &ST) {
5842 switch (ST.getGeneration()) {
5843 default:
5844 break;
5845 case AMDGPUSubtarget::SOUTHERN_ISLANDS:
5846 case AMDGPUSubtarget::SEA_ISLANDS:
5847 return SIEncodingFamily::SI;
5848 case AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS:
5849 case AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX9:
5850 return SIEncodingFamily::VI;
5851 case AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX10:
5852 return SIEncodingFamily::GFX10;
5853 }
5854 llvm_unreachable("Unknown subtarget generation!");
5855}
5856
5857int SIInstrInfo::pseudoToMCOpcode(int Opcode) const {
5858 SIEncodingFamily Gen = subtargetEncodingFamily(ST);
5859
5860 if ((get(Opcode).TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::renamedInGFX9) != 0 &&
5861 ST.getGeneration() == AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX9)
5862 Gen = SIEncodingFamily::GFX9;
5863
5864 // Adjust the encoding family to GFX80 for D16 buffer instructions when the
5865 // subtarget has UnpackedD16VMem feature.
5866 // TODO: remove this when we discard GFX80 encoding.
5867 if (ST.hasUnpackedD16VMem() && (get(Opcode).TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::D16Buf))
5868 Gen = SIEncodingFamily::GFX80;
5869
5870 if (get(Opcode).TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::SDWA) {
5871 switch (ST.getGeneration()) {
5872 default:
5873 Gen = SIEncodingFamily::SDWA;
5874 break;
5875 case AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX9:
5876 Gen = SIEncodingFamily::SDWA9;
5877 break;
5878 case AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX10:
5879 Gen = SIEncodingFamily::SDWA10;
5880 break;
5881 }
5882 }
5883
5884 int MCOp = AMDGPU::getMCOpcode(Opcode, Gen);
5885
5886 // -1 means that Opcode is already a native instruction.
5887 if (MCOp == -1)
5888 return Opcode;
5889
5890 // (uint16_t)-1 means that Opcode is a pseudo instruction that has
5891 // no encoding in the given subtarget generation.
5892 if (MCOp == (uint16_t)-1)
5893 return -1;
5894
5895 return MCOp;
5896}

5898static
5899TargetInstrInfo::RegSubRegPair getRegOrUndef(const MachineOperand &RegOpnd) {
5900 assert(RegOpnd.isReg());
5901 return RegOpnd.isUndef() ? TargetInstrInfo::RegSubRegPair() :
5902 getRegSubRegPair(RegOpnd);

5904
5905TargetInstrInfo::RegSubRegPair
5906llvm::getRegSequenceSubReg(MachineInstr &MI, unsigned SubReg) {
5907 assert(MI.isRegSequence());
5908 for (unsigned I = 0, E = (MI.getNumOperands() - 1)/ 2; I < E; ++I)
5909 if (MI.getOperand(1 + 2 * I + 1).getImm() == SubReg) {
5910 auto &RegOp = MI.getOperand(1 + 2 * I);
5911 return getRegOrUndef(RegOp);
5912 }
5913 return TargetInstrInfo::RegSubRegPair();
5914}
5915
5916// Try to find the definition of reg:subreg in subreg-manipulation pseudos
5917// Following a subreg of reg:subreg isn't supported
5918static bool followSubRegDef(MachineInstr &MI,
5919 TargetInstrInfo::RegSubRegPair &RSR) {
5920 if (!RSR.SubReg)
5921 return false;
5922 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
5923 default: break;
5924 case AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE:
5925 RSR = getRegSequenceSubReg(MI, RSR.SubReg);
5926 return true;
5927 // EXTRACT_SUBREG ins't supported as this would follow a subreg of subreg
5928 case AMDGPU::INSERT_SUBREG:
5929 if (RSR.SubReg == (unsigned)MI.getOperand(3).getImm())
5930 // inserted the subreg we're looking for
5931 RSR = getRegOrUndef(MI.getOperand(2));
5932 else { // the subreg in the rest of the reg
5933 auto R1 = getRegOrUndef(MI.getOperand(1));
5934 if (R1.SubReg) // subreg of subreg isn't supported
5935 return false;
5936 RSR.Reg = R1.Reg;
5937 }
5938 return true;
5939 }
5940 return false;
5941}
5942
5943MachineInstr *llvm::getVRegSubRegDef(const TargetInstrInfo::RegSubRegPair &P,
5944 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) {
5945 assert(MRI.isSSA());
5946 if (!TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(P.Reg))
5947 return nullptr;
5948
5949 auto RSR = P;
5950 auto *DefInst = MRI.getVRegDef(RSR.Reg);
5951 while (auto *MI = DefInst) {
5952 DefInst = nullptr;
5953 switch (MI->getOpcode()) {
5954 case AMDGPU::COPY:
5955 case AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32: {
5956 auto &Op1 = MI->getOperand(1);
5957 if (Op1.isReg() &&
5958 TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(Op1.getReg())) {
5959 if (Op1.isUndef())
5960 return nullptr;
5961 RSR = getRegSubRegPair(Op1);
5962 DefInst = MRI.getVRegDef(RSR.Reg);
5963 }
5964 break;
5965 }
5966 default:
5967 if (followSubRegDef(*MI, RSR)) {
5968 if (!RSR.Reg)
5969 return nullptr;
5970 DefInst = MRI.getVRegDef(RSR.Reg);
5971 }
5972 }
5973 if (!DefInst)
5974 return MI;
5975 }
5976 return nullptr;
5977}
5978
5979bool llvm::isEXECMaskConstantBetweenDefAndUses(unsigned VReg,
5980 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) {
5981 assert(MRI.isSSA() && "Must be run on SSA");
5982 auto *TRI = MRI.getTargetRegisterInfo();
5983
5984 auto *DefI = MRI.getVRegDef(VReg);
5985 auto *BB = DefI->getParent();
5986
5987 DenseSet<MachineInstr*> Uses;
5988 for (auto &Use : MRI.use_nodbg_operands(VReg)) {
5989 auto *I = Use.getParent();
5990 if (I->getParent() != BB)
5991 return false;
5992 Uses.insert(I);
5993 }
5994
5995 auto E = BB->end();
5996 for (auto I = std::next(DefI->getIterator()); I != E; ++I) {
5997 Uses.erase(&*I);
5998 // don't check the last use
5999 if (Uses.empty() || I->modifiesRegister(AMDGPU::EXEC, TRI))
6000 break;
6001 }
6002 return Uses.empty();
6003}
